{"id": "51516", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51516", "title": "Masterworking", "text": "Masterworking is a crafting system in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", introduced in .\nMasterworking is an end-game crafting system, where players use materials earned from &lt;a href=\"the%20Pit%20of%20Artificers\"&gt;the Pit of Artificers&lt;/a&gt; to upgrade their &lt;a href=\"weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;. Masterworking improves the overall strength of all affixes on a weapon, and at every 4th tier, massively upgrades one of its equipped affixes. The affix that receives the bonus will turn Blue. If the same affix is improved again, it will change to Yellow, and in rare cases, it will turn Orange if improved a third time."}
{"id": "34052", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34052", "title": "Mastery Pennants", "text": "Mastery Pennants are &lt;a href=\"cosmetic\"&gt;cosmetic&lt;/a&gt; rewards in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" that can be worn on the character's back, accessed through &lt;a href=\"Wardrobe\"&gt;Wardrobe&lt;/a&gt;. Only one Pennant can be equipped at a time.\nThere are a total of 7 Mastery Pennants, one for each class. They all have different shape, color and symbols.\n\"Wear your brutal heritage proudly.\"\n\"Let all see the humility with which you serve your faith!\"\n\"Single minded vengeance need not be ugly.\"\n\"Your martial prowess shall be worshipped alongside your 1001 gods.\"\n\"All who oppose you, beware.\"\n\"Summoning dead souls to do your bidding does not make you a bad person.\"\n\"A stylish addition to your dashing wardrobe.\"\nEach pennant is awarded if the player beats all four of their class's &lt;a href=\"Set%20Dungeon\"&gt;Set Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;s with Mastery rating. &lt;a href=\"Ascendant%20Pennants\"&gt;Ascendant Pennants&lt;/a&gt; are awarded for the same task, but with either Normal or Mastery rating.\nThe pennants may be worn regardless of class (though earning them is impossible without having a character of the specific class)."}
