{"id": "32134", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32134", "title": "Max Schaefer", "text": "Max Schaefer is a former member of &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20North\"&gt;Blizzard North&lt;/a&gt;, and brother of &lt;a href=\"Erich%20Schaefer\"&gt;Erich Schaefer&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nAlongside his brother and &lt;a href=\"David%20Brevik\"&gt;David Brevik&lt;/a&gt;, Schaefer was one of the founders of Condor, later known as &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20North\"&gt;Blizzard North&lt;/a&gt;. The three had previously worked together at FM Waves, where they worked on \"&lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gordo_106\"&gt;Gordo 106&lt;/a&gt;\".\nSchaefer worked on both \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\" and its &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;sequel&lt;/a&gt;. In the latter, he was in charge of the background team, which designed the appearance of the game's locations.\nAlongside his brother, Schaefer founded &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flagship_Studios\"&gt;Flagship Studios&lt;/a&gt;, and later, &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Runic_Games\"&gt;Runic Games&lt;/a&gt;. After Runic was shut down, he joined Echtra Games, continuing to work on the \"Torchlight\" series."}
