{"id": "21385", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21385", "title": "Maximus", "text": "Maximus is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Two-handed%20swords\"&gt;two-handed sword&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 60 to drop.\nThe unique legendary power summons a sword-bearing demon (model based on &lt;a href=\"Oppressor\"&gt;Oppressor&lt;/a&gt;) for 15 seconds. He engages the closest enemy in melee combat, dealing 100% of the master's damage as &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and being able to draw the enemy attention to himself for quite a long time. The bearer of the sword and the demon are linked with a &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Chains\"&gt;chain of fire&lt;/a&gt; that causes roughly 100-150% Fire damage every 0.25 seconds on touch, to a total of 400-600% damage per second. Both types of damage can &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Hit\"&gt;critically hit&lt;/a&gt;, but do not benefit from elemental damage bonus.\nOnly one slave can be summoned at a time, but there appears to be no &lt;a href=\"internal%20cooldown\"&gt;internal cooldown&lt;/a&gt;. The power works perfectly with &lt;a href=\"Followers\"&gt;Followers&lt;/a&gt;, specifically &lt;a href=\"Eirena\"&gt;Eirena&lt;/a&gt;; if she has it equipped, the fire chains will connect \"her\" and the demon, not the player.\nStats (Level 60).\nMaximus always comes with a bonus to Fire skill damage, which is not normally found on weapons. This Magic Property cannot be replaced by &lt;a href=\"Enchanting\"&gt;Enchanting&lt;/a&gt;."}
