{"id": "4153", "revid": "25014340", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4153", "title": "Meditation", "text": "Meditation is a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"With the observance of this aura, the Paladin supplicates himself to the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt; with silent utterances of prayers. It is in these times of silent worship that the Paladin is rejuvenated in spirit.\"\nGeneral Information.\nMeditation greatly increases Mana regeneration. Even at level 1, it gives 75% (the same effect as a Mana Recharge &lt;a href=\"Shrines%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;shrine&lt;/a&gt;), and can greatly extend the amount of time a caster can spend casting spells before needing to stop and use a mana potion. Even Paladins who are not dedicated to supporting party members can use this intermittently to ease mana upkeep, but this is especially powerful in the hands of a healing paladin, due to the fact that it also gives the same effect as the Paladin's &lt;a href=\"Prayer\"&gt;Prayer&lt;/a&gt; aura at no mana cost.\nMeditation stacks with all other sources of Mana regeneration, including items, &lt;a href=\"Warmth\"&gt;Warmth&lt;/a&gt;, and Mana Recharge Shrines.\nMeditation choice is popular with other party members such as &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt;. It also comes helpful if Paladin himself relies on Mana-consuming attacks from the &lt;a href=\"Combat%20Skills%20%28Paladin%29\"&gt;Combat Skills&lt;/a&gt; list.\nThe &lt;a href=\"runeword\"&gt;runeword&lt;/a&gt; grants a level 12-17 Meditation aura to its wielder, making it a popular &lt;a href=\"hireling\"&gt;hireling&lt;/a&gt; weapon choice for Mana-hungry builds."}
