{"id": "42425", "revid": "52469887", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42425", "title": "Memory of Caldesann", "text": "The Memory of Caldesann is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiography.\n&lt;a href=\"Caldesann\"&gt;Caldesann&lt;/a&gt; and his fellow &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; imbued their &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; in a crystal during the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Exile\"&gt;Dark Exile&lt;/a&gt;, storing their memories for future Horadrim. \nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; awoke Caldesann's memory, under direction by the &lt;a href=\"Memory%20of%20Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Memory of Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Memory of Caldesann appears as an NPC in the &lt;a href=\"Sanctum%20of%20Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Sanctum of Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt;, once the player has inserted &lt;a href=\"Caldesann%27s%20Compassion\"&gt;Caldesann's Compassion&lt;/a&gt; into the shrine.\nHe is simply called \"Caldesann\" in-game, but has been given the \"Memory\" moniker to distinguish him from the &lt;a href=\"Caldesann\"&gt;original&lt;/a&gt;.\nTale.\n\"Wasn't good at naught but war, so I made it my job. &lt;a href=\"Xiansai\"&gt;Xiansai&lt;/a&gt; was divided at the time. Felt right, cleaning up someone else's mess. The company got sent to &lt;a href=\"Chizu\"&gt;Chizu&lt;/a&gt; with simple orders: conscript everyone of fighting age, or sack the place. It was a bunch of settled bandits, we heard; violent against their neighbors, accompanied their robberies with mass conflagrations. So we weren't surprised when we marched in, made our demands, and instead of saying \"no,\" somebody tossed a fire pot at the guy right in front of me. Burst into flame instantly, before he could scream. More of them threw. We were fighting with our clothes and hair catching on fire; &lt;a href=\"horse\"&gt;horse&lt;/a&gt;s were dragging their riders to death along the ground.\"\n\"Four of us barged in. There was a little girl there, small like a mouse, with stringy hair, but otherwise it was empty. We all stood around, looking dumb; then &lt;a href=\"Shunsek\"&gt;Shunsek&lt;/a&gt; started to turn, but something about her hands shaking--like anticipation--stopped me. Only thing saved my life.\"\n\"Next I knew, she had one of those fire pots in her right hand and the plug in the other, and she was about to pour it right in the middle of us. I just shouted at her \"stop!\" \"please\" and maybe it's because I didn't have my sword out, or maybe she could see how scared I was, but she stopped. I thought we'd averted disaster; that's how na\u00efve I was.\"\n\"Shunshek put his hands over the potion and Tsanag and Gaztya had the girl by the hair, and both of them took their knives out. I don't remember what I said to them. It wasn't impressive. Probably just how she was just a kid. They told me to leave if I didn't wanna watch.\"\n\"Everything felt slow then. I tried to get them to stop but they were already holding her to the ground. I rounded on them, someone cut me bad, right over my eyes, and everything was red. When you know who the enemy is, and you're that close, you just start swinging and hope for the best.\""}
{"id": "43993", "revid": "52469887", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43993", "title": "Memory of Cathan", "text": "The Memory of Cathan is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiography.\n&lt;a href=\"Cathan\"&gt;Cathan&lt;/a&gt; and her fellow &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; imbued their &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; in a crystal during the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Exile\"&gt;Dark Exile&lt;/a&gt;, storing their memories for future Horadrim. \nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; awoke Cathan's memory, under direction by the &lt;a href=\"Memory%20of%20Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Memory of Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Memory of Cathan appears as part of the &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20the%20Horadrim\"&gt;Legacy of the Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; system. \nHer in-game description is simply \"Cathan,\" but has been called \"Memory of\" here to distinguish her from her progenitor.\nTale.\n\"Before false pilgrims insisted on ornate prayer chambers and \"donations,\" the annals of &lt;a href=\"Zakara\"&gt;Zakara&lt;/a&gt; were read freely in the city of &lt;a href=\"Tuvant\"&gt;Tuvant&lt;/a&gt;. Even as a girl, I could see the city's changes were not always just, so I made a vow to live simply, without wealth. I left to become a farmhand, and my neighbors worked beside me for decades, until they found &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt;.\"\n\"They discovered a rich vein in the cave behind my field. I remember their excitement... then their confusion when I refused to have the gold mined, and asked my husband to board the cave shut. I knew what came of unexpected riches. My neighbors did not. After a few days, avaricious youths followed me, jeering me every time I passed through the common land.\"\n\"The whole hamlet was aware that I held to a vow of humility. I told my neighbors that, as &lt;a href=\"Akarat\"&gt;Akarat&lt;/a&gt; had said, \"true richness is richness of spirit.\" They maligned my words. Some threatened to claim the gold by force. I began to doubt--was it my place to keep others humble? Could my spareness drive them to evil as surely as any wealth?\"\n\"Traders from Tuvant came seeking to buy a claim; hearing that I would not bend, they spoke with my husband, Okor, and my daughter Joricia. When they had left, Joricia said I could not make her keep my oath. I would accept the traders' offers, she told me, or she would go to the cave and take her due. My husband, with whom I had been bound in love, not faith, nodded. I was heartbroken even before I refused.\"\n\"My family left without saying goodbye, having shattered the boards blocking the cave and taken what little of the gold they could chip away. The next day, my neighbors arrived at my shanty at dawn, demanding to know why I had broken my promise. They called me craven, forked-tongue; they raised axes, threatened to burn my home, and insisted upon \"their\" gold.\""}
{"id": "42403", "revid": "52469887", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42403", "title": "Memory of Iben Fahd", "text": "The Memory of Iben Fahd is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiography.\n&lt;a href=\"Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt; and his fellow &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; imbued their &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; in a crystal during the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Exile\"&gt;Dark Exile&lt;/a&gt;, storing their memories for future Horadrim. \nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, Fahd contacted a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;hero&lt;/a&gt;, guiding them to a fountain in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;. Solving Fahd's riddle, the memory presented itself to the hero, and subsequently guided them to the &lt;a href=\"Iben%20Fahd%27s%20Sanctum\"&gt;sanctum&lt;/a&gt; of his progenitor. He instructed them how to complete the trials that awaited them, and how to gather more power from vessels that contained other Horadric memories.\nIn-game.\nThe Memory of Iben Fahd initiates the \" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"Diablo Immortal\", and appears as an NPC once the player solves the fountain puzzle in Westmarch. He is one of a number of Horadric memories that plays a role in the &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20the%20Horadrim\"&gt;Legacy of the Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; system.\nHis in-game description later shifts to simply \"Iben Fahd.\" He becomes an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Iben%20Fahd%27s%20Sanctum\"&gt;Iben Fahd's Sanctum&lt;/a&gt; once players have installed &lt;a href=\"Iben%20Fahd%27s%20Tenacity\"&gt;Iben Fahd's Tenacity&lt;/a&gt;.\nTale.\n\"I had long since accepted &lt;a href=\"Morrick\"&gt;Morrick&lt;/a&gt;'s invitation to the pit fights he hosted. He was my superior within the &lt;a href=\"Ammuit%20clan\"&gt;Ammuit clan&lt;/a&gt;, and the fights in his complex in &lt;a href=\"Gea%20Kul\"&gt;Gea Kul&lt;/a&gt; were simple, violent expurgations--thrilling, in their reality, to those of us whose &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;spellwork&lt;/a&gt; crossed the boundary between illusion and truth.\"\n\"That night, as the last fighting-bell resounded and the combatants rested from their wounds, I found my eye drawn to commingled &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt; and sweat in the pit, and watched a puddle sink through the concavity in the ground, remarked by the other guests. Where it dripped below, I saw white teeth gleam in a glistening red snout. The blood vanished with a puff of sand and an awful guzzling noise.\"\n\"For minutes, I barely moved. What I had seen, I was sure, was blood sacrifice--a red beast, crouching in illusion below the earth, drinking the life of Morrick's thralls. I retreated, and did not return until I had the Ammuit council at my back. But Morrick, raking both hands through his elaborate braids, parried my every accusation. His fighters were volunteers, he swore. No red demon feasted upon them. What sacrifice could there be?\"\n\"I searched the pit and pulled up piles of earth; I cut my palm open and let the blood drip uselessly upon the sand. The red beast remained hidden, and Morrick was outraged. The council deemed me a menace, and I was stripped of my titles among the Ammuit, and the many artifacts I had won in my journeys. I could have lashed out at Morrick, but I had no hope to defeat him directly, and I could not even unearth his illusion. He was the greater.\"\n\"At that time, old conflicts among the mage clans were as badges of honor. I pledged myself to clan &lt;a href=\"Ennead\"&gt;Ennead&lt;/a&gt; in their black-leaved grotto; so great was their desire to insult my order that they accepted. And I found their perspective inspiring. Unlike we Ammuit, who strove to create fully-formed and perfect illusions all at once, the Ennead artificers imbued their creations one piece at a time. Thus I underwent their ritual transfusions, despite my unease at letting old rivals open my veins.\""}
{"id": "43533", "revid": "52469887", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43533", "title": "Memory of Jered Cain", "text": "The Memory of Jered Cain is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiography.\n&lt;a href=\"Jered%20Cain\"&gt;Jered Cain&lt;/a&gt; and his fellow &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; imbued their &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; in a crystal during the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Exile\"&gt;Dark Exile&lt;/a&gt;, storing their memories for future Horadrim. \nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; awoke Cain's memory, under direction by the &lt;a href=\"Memory%20of%20Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Memory of Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Memory of Jered Cain appears as part of the &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20the%20Horadrim\"&gt;Legacy of the Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; system. \nHis in-game description is simply \"Jered Cain,\" but has been called \"Memory of\" here to distinguish him from his progenitor.\nTale.\n\"Though I had seen 10 summers, my family knew my perspicacity; since I was a child, my sisters had asked after spare vellum for me, and my father bargained for parchment from travelers. They heeded my words when the plague swept through our town, and remained healthy while others fell to the disease, with awful sores blossoming in their mouths and underarms.\"\n\"I wrapped my face in wet rags, watched the burning of the cadavers, and spoke to the relatives of the dead about their lives. My notes I kept in a small wood and leather tome, which I thought of as my grimoire. When I saw someone walking to the granaries or taverns, I urged them to stay outdoors, away from fouled air and the feverish, and to leech out bad blood. I was only a boy; seldom, it seemed, did they listen.\"\n\"Terror, you see, was worse than the plague. The plague killed neighbors and friends; terror killed reason itself. Our home was safe, near the edge of town, and yet my family was the subject of angry questions. Why were we spared? What witch's pact had we made? What was in that tome I read? As the plague continued, the hysteria of the questions grew. Neighbors stared at us. My sisters' faces were fearful always.\""}
{"id": "44027", "revid": "52469887", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44027", "title": "Memory of Nilfur", "text": "The Memory of Nilfur is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiography.\n&lt;a href=\"Nilfur\"&gt;Nilfur&lt;/a&gt; and her fellow &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; imbued their &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; in a crystal during the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Exile\"&gt;Dark Exile&lt;/a&gt;, storing their memories for future Horadrim. \nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; awoke Nilfur's memory, under direction by the &lt;a href=\"Memory%20of%20Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Memory of Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Memory of Nilfur appears as part of the &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20the%20Horadrim\"&gt;Legacy of the Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; system. \nHer in-game description is simply \"Nilfur,\" but has been called \"Memory of\" here to distinguish him from his progenitor.\nTale.\n\"In the citadel of &lt;a href=\"Ullrat\"&gt;Ullrat&lt;/a&gt;, the emperor's lords-myrmidon executed his will\u2014but in matters of actual power, they were children. Thus, when they clashed with &lt;a href=\"Aphod\"&gt;Aphod&lt;/a&gt;'s armies, they begged the &lt;a href=\"Zann%20Esu\"&gt;Zann Esu&lt;/a&gt; for advisement, and I deigned to attend them. It had been a week since a blockade of cavalry and arrow held us trapped together in Ullrat's palace, and commoners in their homes. The thirst-deaths had begun.\"\n\"Corpses lay in the streets with their skin shriveled. The two lords-myrmidon, Kalbaz and Isshai, looked down at them; safe, yet filled with fear. Isshai seemed disquiet, despite how often he had advised war with Aphod. He begged me, \"great Nilfur, will you call upon your magic and strike down the invaders?\" I held my hand up to bid him silent. I could hear the walls splintering.\"\n\"Aphod's armies brought a great rock-hurler; where it struck, timber and stone walls were tossed about like twigs. I knew injury would be plentiful, homes destroyed. Spake Isshai again, \"Mighty Nilfur, you must yoke the storm and take the invaders' lives!\" Kalbaz said nothing--he feared my magic would bring other mages--but Isshai was insistent, and thus I replied: \"No, for the enemy's weakness has not been revealed.\"\"\n\"Before sunset, the armies of Aphod were inside the city. They fought with inhuman zeal, clambering up ladders in full suits of jagged armor. I studied them with eagles' eyes, my vision piercing through their helmets so that I could see the answer I sought upon the face of the enemy. But all I saw were people.\"\n\"Aphod's soldiers stood upon the heaps of dead to surmount the walls separating Ullrat into quarters. Fighting beneath these walls led to collapses; hundreds were trapped and mortally wounded. The enemy vanguard pushed our despondent army to the exterior of the palace, and took up ramsheads to breach it. \"Nilfur,\" Isshai cried, \"will you not act?\""}
{"id": "43761", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43761", "title": "Memory of Nor Tiraj", "text": "The Memory of Nor Tiraj is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiography.\n&lt;a href=\"Nor%20Tiraj\"&gt;Nor Tiraj&lt;/a&gt; and his fellow &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; imbued their &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; in a crystal during the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Exile\"&gt;Dark Exile&lt;/a&gt;, storing their memories for future Horadrim. \nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; awoke Tiraj's memory, under direction by the &lt;a href=\"Memory%20of%20Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Memory of Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Memory of Nor Tiraj appears as part of the &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20the%20Horadrim\"&gt;Legacy of the Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; system. \nHis in-game description is simply \"Nor Tiraj,\" but has been called \"Memory of\" here to distinguish him from his progenitor.\nTale.\n\"I fell in with deserters in my youth, just for the company. As we traveled west I warned them not to settle in the &lt;a href=\"Lukotori%20Fens\"&gt;Lukotori Fens&lt;/a&gt;, but only a few agreed, and the rest found my tone ominous and overbearing. They were soldiers and their kin, used to hard living. Now I had brought them to a cave to tell them they would all be dead within the week.\"\n\"The dozen wept as I showed them pictograms on the walls, depicting shovels, upturned earth, and a wicked specter, with long hair draped over it like clothing, standing astride bones. A couple, &lt;a href=\"Emaigh\"&gt;Emaigh&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Gloffin\"&gt;Gloffin&lt;/a&gt;, had guilty expressions\u2014they had dug simple trenches on the swamp's western side. They had not meant to disturb, but one cannot know what lies beneath one's feet.\"\n\"After Emaigh and Gloffin broke the earth, their two children were visited by the specter on the wall; it passed a hand through their faces and marked them. The cave artist had drawn pairs of eyes with the irises filled, and the eyes of the children had become dim, unnatural amber. Emaigh and Gloffin were sure that killing the specter would save them, but I saw no victory displayed on the wall. Yet I went forth with them that night, for I am Nor Tiraj.\""}
{"id": "43542", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43542", "title": "Memory of Tal Rasha", "text": "The Memory of Tal Rasha is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiography.\n&lt;a href=\"Tal%20Rasha\"&gt;Tal Rasha&lt;/a&gt; and his fellow &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; imbued their &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; in a crystal during the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Exile\"&gt;Dark Exile&lt;/a&gt;, storing their memories for future Horadrim. \nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; awoke Cain's memory, under direction by the &lt;a href=\"Memory%20of%20Iben%20Fahd\"&gt;Memory of Iben Fahd&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Memory of Jered Cain appears as part of the &lt;a href=\"Legacy%20of%20the%20Horadrim\"&gt;Legacy of the Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; system. \nHis in-game description is simply \"Tal Rasha,\" but has been called \"Memory of\" here to distinguish him from his progenitor.\nTale.\n\"When I was younger, I visited the court of &lt;a href=\"Coshumat\"&gt;Coshumat&lt;/a&gt;, the Halfwit Count. I bestowed that name upon him because he ruled over starving fiefs, yet refused bread and succor to those who did not impress him. All that impressed him was trial by combat.\"\n\"Coshumat kept a retinue of ten burly show fighters he called the &lt;a href=\"Eminents\"&gt;Eminents&lt;/a&gt;. As I arrived, they had just finished with a man who begged relief for his village after a poor harvest. The count asked him to endure thirty strikes from the Eminents, and watched attentively as they beat the man unconscious with the flats of their &lt;a href=\"swords\"&gt;swords&lt;/a&gt;.\""}
