{"id": "20731", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20731", "title": "Mempo of Twilight", "text": "Mempo of Twilight is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Helms\"&gt;helm&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 60 to drop.\nThe Mempo received a unique Legendary power in &lt;a href=\"Patch%202.7.4\"&gt;Patch 2.7.4&lt;/a&gt;, almost 10 years after it was first released with the launch of \"Diablo III\" itself. The update shifted it from a general use item to a &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;-associated one, although it is still wearable by other classes. Its damage bonus to &lt;a href=\"Meteor\"&gt;Meteor&lt;/a&gt; is intended to synergize well with the set, which was updated to be Meteor-focused at the same time. The damage bonus of the legendary power does work with the Meteors triggered by the set, although the Meteor Shower rune effect only applies to Meteors directly cast by the player.\nPrior to receiving its unique power, the Mempo of Twilight was considered to have reliably strong stats due to its guaranteed &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Speed\"&gt;Attack Speed&lt;/a&gt; - which does not appear randomly on helms in general - &lt;a href=\"Primary%20stat\"&gt;Primary stat&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Resistances\"&gt;Resistances&lt;/a&gt; to all, and &lt;a href=\"socket\"&gt;socket&lt;/a&gt;. Unusually, all four of the Primary Magic Properties are guaranteed rather than chosen randomly, leaving &lt;a href=\"Enchanting\"&gt;Enchanting&lt;/a&gt; the only way to obtain alternative bonuses on the helm."}
