{"id": "1946", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1946", "title": "Meshif", "text": "Meshif is a ship captain.\nBiography.\nMeshif was born in &lt;a href=\"Kurast\"&gt;Kurast&lt;/a&gt;, where he spent his childhood. He made port runs around the &lt;a href=\"Twin%20Seas\"&gt;Twin Seas&lt;/a&gt; and occasionally out to &lt;a href=\"Kingsport\"&gt;Kingsport&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;. He also sailed across &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;'s southern seas and visited many strange lands. Whenever he stopped in &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Elzix\"&gt;Elzix&lt;/a&gt; offered him a free room in his inn. However, Meshif preferred the comforts of his own cabin. Similarly, he rarely frequented &lt;a href=\"Atma\"&gt;Atma&lt;/a&gt;'s establishment. &lt;a href=\"Lysander\"&gt;Lysander&lt;/a&gt; sold him many sea-sickness potions over the years, as many of his passengers didn't take well to the rocking of his ship.\nAt some point he had an encounter with an &lt;a href=\"Amazon%20Caste\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt;.\nLut Gholein.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231264\"&gt;1264&lt;/a&gt;, Sultan &lt;a href=\"Jerhyn\"&gt;Jerhyn&lt;/a&gt; ordered Meshif to stay docked in &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt; in case of emergency, as the city dealt with the appearance of &lt;a href=\"monsters\"&gt;strange creatures&lt;/a&gt; in the desert outside the city. He obliged, though he knew that there was something that Jerhyn wasn't telling him; things in Lut Gholein didn't appear that bad to his eye. He came into contact with a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; who were persuing the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wanderer\"&gt;Dark Wanderer&lt;/a&gt;.\nEventually it came to light that &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s had gained access to Lut Gholein through a portal in Jerhyn's palace, hence why he had asked Meshif to stay. The heroes were able to deal with the issue, and Jerhyn asked Meshif to wait some more, in case they needed to get out of the city. Eventually, at Jerhyn's request, he took them east to &lt;a href=\"Kurast\"&gt;Kurast&lt;/a&gt;.\nKurast.\nMeshif sailed into Kurast, finding to his dismay that the city was being overtaken by jungle; that he had boasted of the &lt;a href=\"town\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt; on the journey to his home was a tragedy not lost on him. The heroes were able to defeat &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt; however, and the jungle began to retreat. He thanked them, stating that Kurast could now begin to reclaim its former glory.\nScouring Sands.\nDecades after the events of the fall of the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evil\"&gt;Prime Evils&lt;/a&gt; as well the aftermath against &lt;a href=\"Malthael\"&gt;Malthael&lt;/a&gt;, an old Meshif since retired from being a ship captain and his days of adventures, and moved back to &lt;a href=\"Kehjistan\"&gt;Kehjistan&lt;/a&gt;. he spends most of his days at the Argentek Riverbank near to Tarsarak.\nHe would be eventually visited by &lt;a href=\"Lorath%20Nahr\"&gt;Lorath Nahr&lt;/a&gt; and the wanderer hero, who would request aid to cross a harsh sandstorm on the way to &lt;a href=\"Elias\"&gt;Elias&lt;/a&gt;' haven for &lt;a href=\"Lilith\"&gt;Lilith&lt;/a&gt;'s cult. He often confuses Elias for Deckard Cain, reminiscing on their adventures decades ago and never knowing what happened to the Last Horadrim.\nAfter crossing the desert and arriving at The Outer Gardens, Meshif would remain outside, hiding. However, he is killed by cultists after Lorath steals the &lt;a href=\"Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Sightless Eye&lt;/a&gt; from Elias.\nIn-game.\nDiablo II.\nMeshif appears in acts &lt;a href=\"Act%20II%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;II&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Act%20III%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;III&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". He takes the player from &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Kurast\"&gt;Kurast&lt;/a&gt;, bridging the two acts.\nMeshif is the sailor who takes the player from &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Kurast\"&gt;Kurast&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn the latter, he trades the hero &lt;a href=\"The%20Golden%20Bird%20%28Item%29\"&gt;The Golden Bird&lt;/a&gt; for a &lt;a href=\"Jade%20Figurine\"&gt;Jade Figurine&lt;/a&gt; found in quest. In the above mentioned quest, it is shown that he owns a figurine collection which was missing the Jade Figurine, which the player gives to him.\nUnlike &lt;a href=\"Warriv\"&gt;Warriv&lt;/a&gt;, he does not change clothes between acts.\nDialogue.\n\"Main article: &lt;a href=\"Meshif/Dialogue\"&gt;Meshif/Dialogue&lt;/a&gt;\"\nDiablo IV.\nMeshif appears during Act III of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". He aids &lt;a href=\"Lorath%20Nahr\"&gt;Lorath&lt;/a&gt; and hero as a guide to cross through a sandstorm to the Outer Gardens, to find &lt;a href=\"Elias\"&gt;Elias&lt;/a&gt;. After Meshif dies, the wanderer hero inherits his sword as a memento.\nPersonality and Traits.\nMeshif appears to be a follower of the &lt;a href=\"Skatsim\"&gt;Skatsim&lt;/a&gt; faith. He had no desire to be immortal, stating \"can you imagine having to wake up every night just to piss for the next thousand years?\" &lt;a href=\"Fara\"&gt;Fara&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Jerhyn\"&gt;Jerhyn&lt;/a&gt; held him in high regard.\nIn \"Diablo IV\", now an old man, he has since became a drunkard, and has gone slightly senile; when first meeting Lorath, he confuses him for &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt;, and continuously call him \"Deckard\" even after Lorath corrects him and states that Deckard has died. Meshif longs for his old days of adventures, and promptly agrees to help Lorath and the hero. The denizens of Tarsarak call him strange. Meshif has a camel called Isabella; after his death, Lorath takes her."}
