{"id": "38575", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38575", "title": "Meteor (Diablo IV)", "text": "Meteor\u00a0is a Mastery Fire spell used by\u00a0\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". It is a remake of the classic &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Meteor%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;spell of the same name&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThis spell works similar to the previous incarnations, summoning a meteor that blasts the ground for high Fire damage after a short delay and leaves behind a patch of flames.\nEnemies within the area take Fire damage every second and count as Burning.\nEnchantment effect resembles the &lt;a href=\"Belt%20of%20the%20Trove\"&gt;Belt of the Trove&lt;/a&gt;: it rains Meteors down on random nearby enemies every few seconds, but without any control from the character and without any Mana cost."}
{"id": "37568", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37568", "title": "Meteor (Diablo Immortal)", "text": "Meteor is a &lt;a href=\"Wizard%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt; skill in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". A ball of &lt;a href=\"fire\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; is dropped on enemies, doing high damage over a small area."}
