{"id": "49161", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49161", "title": "Midwinter Blight", "text": "Midwinter Blight was a Christmas-themed event for \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". It launched on December 12, 2023 and lasted until January 2, 2024. It had event-exclusive currencies, rewards, and encounters.\nLore.\nMidwinter Blight is a recurring event of &lt;a href=\"Kyovashad\"&gt;Kyovashad&lt;/a&gt;, held during the deep winter months of the &lt;a href=\"Fractured%20Peaks\"&gt;Fractured Peaks&lt;/a&gt;. It is during this period that the Peaks are stalked by the &lt;a href=\"Blightfiend\"&gt;Blightfiend&lt;/a&gt;s. As such, people gather in Kyovashad. In light, in celebration, in memory of the dead. &lt;a href=\"Midwinter%20Square\"&gt;Midwinter Square&lt;/a&gt; is decorated not only with the effigies of monsters, but heirlooms of the lost. This is not to signal that the people of Kyvoashad are not afraid, but rather a demonstration that when people are afraid, they need each other the most. The event includes music, dancing, and song, in an effort to suppress the people's dread. Some venture out from Kyovashad to face &lt;a href=\"the%20Red-Cloaked%20Horror\"&gt;the Red-Cloaked Horror&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe tradition was apparently suppressed by the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Light\"&gt;Cathedral of Light&lt;/a&gt;, but the tradition was revived in the winter of &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;. The Cathedral wasn't pleased, but the people of Kyovashad wanted a return to their roots. \nGameplay.\nDuring the event, the Fractured Peaks were enveloped by a storm and were in deep winter darkness. The lead &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; for the event was a wandering bard named &lt;a href=\"Gileon\"&gt;Gileon&lt;/a&gt;, which the player met in &lt;a href=\"Kyovashad\"&gt;Kyovashad&lt;/a&gt;. The square was decorated appropriately for the season and featured the Totem of Midwinter. Players battle dagainst &lt;a href=\"Frigid%20Husk\"&gt;Frigid Husk&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Blightfiend\"&gt;Blightfiend&lt;/a&gt;s, who were in service to a &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt; called &lt;a href=\"the%20Red%20Cloaked%20Horror\"&gt;the Red Cloaked Horror&lt;/a&gt;. Defeating enemies and completing area events could summon this &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;.\nSee also.\n&lt;a href=\"Brumaltine\"&gt;Brumaltine&lt;/a&gt;, a similar event celebrated in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;."}
