{"id": "43668", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43668", "title": "Mikayel", "text": "Mikayel is an &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt; NPC in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiography.\nMikayel was the lieutenant of a cadre of angel sentinels led by &lt;a href=\"Verathiel\"&gt;Verathiel&lt;/a&gt;. They discovered the &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Realm of Damnation&lt;/a&gt; as it was taking shape. Cut off from the &lt;a href=\"High%20Heavens\"&gt;High Heavens&lt;/a&gt;, they carved out a &lt;a href=\"the%20Last%20Vestige\"&gt;foothold&lt;/a&gt; in the realm, battling &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s over the eons.\nMikayel was on of the angels from Verathiel's cadre that were captured. He was imprisoned in a bloody cavern in the &lt;a href=\"Plains%20of%20Torment\"&gt;Plains of Torment&lt;/a&gt; and was attached to a &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Siphon\"&gt;Soul Siphon&lt;/a&gt; for his &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt; to be extracted to &lt;a href=\"Pits%20of%20Anguish\"&gt;demonic pits&lt;/a&gt; in order to create more demons for &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt;'s army. The &lt;a href=\"Butcher%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Butcher&lt;/a&gt; was put in charge of his imprisonment and torture. In &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt;(s) encountered him and freed him.\nHe was one of &lt;a href=\"Verathiel\"&gt;the&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Andalon\"&gt;angels&lt;/a&gt; that opened a portal to Skarn's throne room for the hero(es) to battle him. After Skarn's defeat and Verathiel's sacrifice, he opened another portal for the hero(es) to get to &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nMikayel first appears in the main quest \"&lt;a href=\"Carved%20in%20Blood\"&gt;Carved in Blood&lt;/a&gt;\", where the player has to kill the &lt;a href=\"Butcher%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Butcher&lt;/a&gt; in order to free him. His last appearance was in the main quest \"&lt;a href=\"Lord%20of%20Damnation%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Lord of Damnation&lt;/a&gt;\", when he opens a portal for the player to return to Westmarch. He is not seen in the game outside of the quests he appears in."}
