{"id": "17122", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17122", "title": "Mira Eamon", "text": "Mira Eamon was the wife of &lt;a href=\"Haedrig%20Eamon\"&gt;Haedrig Eamon&lt;/a&gt;. She met her end in &lt;a href=\"New%20Tristram\"&gt;New Tristram&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nMeeting Haedrig.\nMira met Haedrig in a town on the outskirts of &lt;a href=\"Kurast\"&gt;Kurast&lt;/a&gt;. She was locked in a cage, to be burnt as a \"&lt;a href=\"witch\"&gt;witch&lt;/a&gt;.\" In the middle of the night, Haedrig broke her out, and they escaped. Her captors didn't chase them far\u2014Haedrig reflected that this was likely because they were pleased to see her go.\nSoon after meeting, the pair passed near &lt;a href=\"Caldeum\"&gt;Caldeum&lt;/a&gt;. She wanted to stop and see the city, but Haedrig convinced her to travel on.\nAt some point after their escape, the pair joined a &lt;a href=\"Vecin\"&gt;Vecin&lt;/a&gt; wagon train. A &lt;a href=\"Mystic%20%28Lore%29\"&gt;Mystic&lt;/a&gt;]] with the Vecin recognized Mira's talent, and taught her. Along the way, Mira and Haedrig fell in love and got married.\nAt some point, on Mira's urging, the couple headed west to &lt;a href=\"Tristram\"&gt;Tristram&lt;/a&gt;. Haedrig would later wonder if Mira had known what her future held, and had willingly led herself to her doom, in order to get Haedrig to a place where he could aid &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;.\nRisen.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231285\"&gt;1285&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; besieged &lt;a href=\"New%20Tristram\"&gt;New Tristram&lt;/a&gt;. Alongside &lt;a href=\"Leah\"&gt;Leah&lt;/a&gt;, she tended the wounded. However, she was bitten, and became noticably ill. It was realized that she had become infected. She was thus thrown into a cellar with people likewise afflicted. During this time, she was able to write a &lt;a href=\"Mira%27s%20Letter%20to%20Haedrig\"&gt;final letter&lt;/a&gt; to her husband.\nWhen &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; came upon her, she was still &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;, and begged for her husband to save her. Shortly afterwards however, the plague set in, and she turned into a &lt;a href=\"Wretched%20Mother\"&gt;Wretched Mother&lt;/a&gt; variant of &lt;a href=\"Risen%20Dead\"&gt;Risen Dead&lt;/a&gt;, leaving The Nephalem with no option but to put her down.\nMira's death continued to haunt Haedrig. During &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;'s assault on the &lt;a href=\"High%20Heavens\"&gt;High Heavens&lt;/a&gt;, a vision of her was used against the Lord of Terror's foes, seeking to strain their resolve.\nIn-game.\nMira appears in the &lt;a href=\"Cellar%20of%20the%20Damned\"&gt;Cellar of the Damned&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Act%20I%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;first act&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"Campaign%20Mode\"&gt;Campaign Mode&lt;/a&gt;, during the quest \"&lt;a href=\"A%20Shattered%20Crown\"&gt;A Shattered Crown&lt;/a&gt;\". She battles &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; as a Super Unique &lt;a href=\"Wretched%20Mother\"&gt;Wretched Mother&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0with the title \"Wife of Haedrig\". In combat, she has the &lt;a href=\"Knockback%20%28monster%20trait%29\"&gt;Knockback&lt;/a&gt; trait and spits empowered, charged up bolts dealing greater &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; damage. Unlike other Wretched Mothers however, she does not vomit new &lt;a href=\"Risen%20Dead\"&gt;Risen Dead&lt;/a&gt;.\nA vision of her sometimes appears later during the &lt;a href=\"Act%20IV%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;fourth act&lt;/a&gt; in the quest &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evil%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Prime Evil&lt;/a&gt;, where she asks the player, \"How could you convince my own husband to kill me? I could have been saved, but you made him cut me down!\". The vision is then revealed to be an illusion of the &lt;a href=\"Aspect%20of%20Lies\"&gt;Aspect of Lies&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt;, Mira is located at a random location within the &lt;a href=\"Festering%20Woods\"&gt;Festering Woods&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0or &lt;a href=\"The%20Weeping%20Hollow\"&gt;The Weeping Hollow&lt;/a&gt;. "}
