{"id": "51623", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51623", "title": "Miray", "text": "Miray was the apprentice of &lt;a href=\"Vithu\"&gt;Vithu&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nAt some point, Miray imagined the &lt;a href=\"Void\"&gt;Void&lt;/a&gt;, and drew it for her parents. Apparently, like Vithu, her painting of the Void drove her parents to commit suicide, as they chased the sublimity of their feelings. While technically guilty of causing the &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;s of her parents, she blamed the Void.\nAt some point after her parents' deaths, Miray approached Vithu. To the seer's surprise, she begged to be his apprentice. Vithu accepted Miray's apprenticeship, and they painted the Void in new colors, undeniable, but robbed of all its power. She eventually eclipsed her mentor's talent, which. She returned home one night to find him gone, and perfectly oval holes cut through the roof and floor of her home.\nIn-game.\nMiray is mentioned in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" in the text flavor of \"&lt;a href=\"Vithu%27s%20Urges\"&gt;Vithu's Urges&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"item%20set\"&gt;item set&lt;/a&gt;."}
