{"id": "9139", "revid": "28784073", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9139", "title": "Mirror Image", "text": "Mirror Image\u00a0is an &lt;a href=\"Arcane\"&gt;Arcane&lt;/a&gt; spell used by\u00a0s\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nMirror Image conjures two illusionary copies of the caster (enemies cannot see which of the three Wizards is real, though they may guess by indirect signs). Images can cast any of the currently equipped spells, except for channeled spells, mirror image, electrocute, or any defensive spell except for frost nova, with reduced damage, though their spells do benefit from runes and enhancements of the Wizard's own skills. They can even summon a . \nWhile damage of the illusions' spells is reduced, the &lt;a href=\"Crowd%20Control\"&gt;Crowd Control&lt;/a&gt; effects they apply last their full duration, that is, using the Duplicates rune combined with allows &lt;a href=\"freeze\"&gt;freezing&lt;/a&gt; enemies across a massive area in one cast.\nCasting a new Mirror Image before the previous ones expire causes the old images to despawn.\nImages summoned by &lt;a href=\"Teleport%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Teleport (Fracture)&lt;/a&gt; are not affected by runes and enhancements of the regular Mirror Image.\nIf the Wizard shifts into &lt;a href=\"Archon\"&gt;Archon&lt;/a&gt; form while the Mirror Images are active, they will despawn.\nSpells cast by Mirror Images have zero &lt;a href=\"proc%20coefficient\"&gt;proc coefficient&lt;/a&gt;.\nMirror Images may cast non-damaging spells, like &lt;a href=\"Slow%20Time\"&gt;Slow Time&lt;/a&gt;. However, they have a limit of how many times they can do so."}
{"id": "26185", "revid": "25771421", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26185", "title": "Mirrorball", "text": "Mirrorball\u00a0is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Source\"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0for the\u00a0\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires\u00a0&lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt;\u00a031 to drop.\nMirrorball is known for effectively doubling (or tripling) the effectiveness of &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Missile\"&gt;Magic Missile&lt;/a&gt;. The additional missiles fly in the same direction, with slightly different angle, effectively in the same way as Split rune of the said skill. With Split rune, only adds 1-2 more missiles, to the total of 4-5 per cast."}
