{"id": "48923", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48923", "title": "Mirto", "text": "Mirto is an old &lt;a href=\"barbarian\"&gt;barbarian&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Fianne\"&gt;Fianne&lt;/a&gt;'s father.\nBiography.\nIn his youth, Mirto was one of the best swordsmen of the &lt;a href=\"Thunder%20Tribe\"&gt;Thunder Tribe&lt;/a&gt;. He was among the Barbarians who fought against the &lt;a href=\"Army%20of%20Destruction\"&gt;Army of Destruction&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231265\"&gt;1265&lt;/a&gt;. Moments before &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Arreat\"&gt;the mountain&lt;/a&gt; was sundered he glimpsed the visage of &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Tyrael&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Archangel\"&gt;Archangel&lt;/a&gt; of Justice. He then took it as his sacred duty to raise a monument to the angel, in order to remind the that the &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt; protected them in their darkest moment.\nAfter that, the tribe made &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Village%20%28Frozen%20Tundra%29\"&gt;a settlement&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt;, where they lived until it was destroyed by &lt;a href=\"Warped%20Ones\"&gt;Warped Ones&lt;/a&gt;,who raided the village at sunrise, catching most of its occupants off guard. He survived along with his daughter, and they relocate to &lt;a href=\"Bitter%20Hearth\"&gt;Bitter Hearth&lt;/a&gt;.\nVision of Justice.\nMirto decided to fulfill his sacred duty. He returned with his daughter and &lt;a href=\"Hrodolf\"&gt;Hrodolf&lt;/a&gt; \u2014 another barbarian from Bitter Hearth, to the Abandoned Village to build the statue.\nIn-game.\nMirto is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". He is featured in the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20Side%20Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Vision%20of%20Justice\"&gt;Vision of Justice&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
