{"id": "1435", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1435", "title": "Miscellaneous Items", "text": "Miscellaneous items are usable &lt;a href=\"items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt; that are not equipped on a character's body via the \"paper doll\" interface. They can be subdivided into consumable items, socketable items, and others. &lt;a href=\"Crafting\"&gt;Crafting&lt;/a&gt; ingredients are not included in this group.\nConsumable items are kept in the player's inventory (or possibly &lt;a href=\"belt%20slot\"&gt;belt slot&lt;/a&gt;s in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\") until they are used. They have limited charges or sometimes just one use. They may be usable via the inventory, belt slots, or hotkeys to select them as skills. Consumable items were cut significantly for \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" and beyond.\nSocketable items can be placed into the &lt;a href=\"socket\"&gt;socket&lt;/a&gt;s of other items, which are usually equippable, for a variety of bonuses. Sockets were introduced in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nOther items include:"}
{"id": "26310", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26310", "title": "Miser's Hovel", "text": "Miser's Hovel is a location in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20Commons\"&gt;Westmarch Commons&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is not guaranteed to appear, but if it does, it will always contain the same-name event.\nInside, there are no enemies, only the three chests for the event, and the lootable corpse of their owner (which drops the tome along with some gold).\nAs of a hotfix for patch 2.1, there is a chance of a pack of &lt;a href=\"Champion%20Monsters\"&gt;Champion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Punisher\"&gt;Punisher&lt;/a&gt;s\u00a0spawning in this area at &lt;a href=\"Torment%20difficulty\"&gt;Torment difficulty&lt;/a&gt;."}
