{"id": "44067", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44067", "title": "Misty Valley", "text": "The Misty Valley is a forest located on &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt; to the north of the &lt;a href=\"Foggy%20Plains\"&gt;Foggy Plains&lt;/a&gt;. Echoes of the dead roam this area and malicious &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28monster%29\"&gt;Nightmares&lt;/a&gt; lurk around to ambush unaware &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s.\nLore.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Silent%20Monastery\"&gt;Silent Monastery&lt;/a&gt; once stood here. Towards the end of the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum%20Crusade\"&gt;Zakarum Crusade&lt;/a&gt;, it was attacked by the &lt;a href=\"Sons%20of%20Rakkis\"&gt;Sons of Rakkis&lt;/a&gt;. In a desperate move, Patriarch &lt;a href=\"Sladyan\"&gt;Sladyan&lt;/a&gt; released a &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Nightmare\"&gt;sealed evil&lt;/a&gt; that covered the whole valley in the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Mists\"&gt;Black Mists&lt;/a&gt;, killing almost everything in it.\nThe Black Fog remains in the Misty Valley, and it is inhabited by Nightmares. The &lt;a href=\"Horadrim\"&gt;Horadrim&lt;/a&gt; built altars that can temporary create sanctuaries of &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt; around themselves in order to provide reprieve for &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s passing through the area.\nBy &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, Mount Zavain was infested by the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Cult of Damnation&lt;/a&gt;. Amongst other areas of the mountain, they built hideouts in ruins and caves found in the Misty Valley.\nIn-game.\nThe Misty Valley is a Mount Zavain zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
