{"id": "26311", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26311", "title": "A Miner's Gold", "text": "A Miner's Gold is an &lt;a href=\"Event%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;event&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20II%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act II&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It takes place on the &lt;a href=\"Howling%20Plateau\"&gt;Howling Plateau&lt;/a&gt;, and a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; is sometimes offered to complete it.\nA complex rig sits atop a deep mineshaft, in which the Treasure of the Nephalem - essentially a &lt;a href=\"Resplendent%20Chest\"&gt;Resplendent Chest&lt;/a&gt; - hangs from a pulley system. The event is started upon talking to a Crazed Miner calling out for assistance next to the rig's activating lever. One wave of &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20One\"&gt;Fallen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Shaman\"&gt;Fallen Shaman&lt;/a&gt; appears when the lever first gets stuck, then after the miner fixes the jam, another follows as the chest is ascending. All monsters must be cleared before the chest can be opened, which completes the event."}
{"id": "42162", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42162", "title": "A Mirrored World", "text": "A Mirrored World is a &lt;a href=\"Library%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Library of Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt; zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nThe Mirrored World is, according to &lt;a href=\"the%20Curator\"&gt;the Curator&lt;/a&gt;, a reflection of &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. The realm is artificial, powered by &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;s that date back to the &lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Magic\"&gt;Age of Magic&lt;/a&gt;. \nAn entrance to this realm was located in a mirror found in the Library of Zoltun Kulle. However, it is unclear whether this world is located inside the mirror, or is beyond it. A skilled mage can transport someone directly to the Mirrored World.\nThe Mirrored World is cold; &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; is present here, apparently operating in a manner unique to this world. It is also home to &lt;a href=\"Hungering%20Echo\"&gt;Hungering Echo&lt;/a&gt;es and other spectral beings, apparently sustained by a rune taken from the &lt;a href=\"Statue%20of%20Resurgence\"&gt;Statue of Resurgence&lt;/a&gt;.\nAt least two individuals have entered the Mirrored World. One made it in and solved its mirror puzzle which would have allowed access to the rune, but was killed by the Hungering Echoes. They survived long enough to provide a warning to future interlopers by writing a message in their own &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt;. The second was &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; who entered the world at the behest of &lt;a href=\"the%20Curator\"&gt;the Curator&lt;/a&gt;. They obtained the rune and defeated the attacking spectral beings.\nShards of the Mirrored World form &lt;a href=\"Sumina%20Glass\"&gt;Sumina Glass&lt;/a&gt;es, which are powered by the &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; of denizens of the realm. The heart of a single realm-lord (an especially powerful denizen of the Mirrored World) is enough to power a piece of Sumina Glass.\nIn-game.\nThe Mirror World becomes accessible during the \"&lt;a href=\"Lost%20Runes\"&gt;Lost Runes&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", when the player is assigned to find the third rune. It is visited again in the \"\" &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "43903", "revid": "51929228", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43903", "title": "A Nice Place to Visit", "text": "A Nice Place to Visit is a &lt;a href=\"Campaign%20Achievements\"&gt;campaign achievement&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" given for exploring specific areas in and around &lt;a href=\"New%20Tristram\"&gt;New Tristram&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "25723", "revid": "13298744", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=25723", "title": "A Page from Lazarus's Grimoire", "text": ""}
{"id": "33664", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33664", "title": "A Plague of Burrowers", "text": "A Plague of Burrowers is a special in &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It can only appear if nominated a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt;, in any zone of any Act. If it appears, one can go through a red &lt;a href=\"portal\"&gt;portal&lt;/a&gt; and access one of the special bounty zones: &lt;a href=\"Leoric%27s%20Gardens\"&gt;Leoric's Gardens&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Blighted%20Sewer\"&gt;Blighted Sewer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"The%20Killing%20Grounds\"&gt;The Killing Grounds&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"The%20Archives\"&gt;The Archives&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"The%20Bound%20Keep\"&gt;The Bound Keep&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"Nephalem%20Proving%20Ground\"&gt;Nephalem Proving Ground&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe event itself requires cleansing a &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Chest\"&gt;Cursed Chest&lt;/a&gt;. Once it is touched, a timer will start, and multiple &lt;a href=\"Scouring%20Lobber\"&gt;Scouring Lobber&lt;/a&gt;s (named Cursed Burrowers) will spawn, any of them, if killed before the timer expires, will spawn an additional one. Once the timer is over, the player must clear any remaining monster, and in the end, kill the &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Matriarch\"&gt;Cursed Matriarch&lt;/a&gt;. If at least 6 Burrowers are killed before time is up, one will receive a bonus &lt;a href=\"Radiant%20Chest\"&gt;Radiant Chest&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "49053", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49053", "title": "A Plague of Hatred", "text": "A Plague of Hatred was the second &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Season%20of%20the%20Malignant\"&gt;Season of the Malignant&lt;/a&gt;\" in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". It leads on directly from \"&lt;a href=\"Burning%20from%20Within\"&gt;Burning from Within&lt;/a&gt;\". To unlock the next quest, \"&lt;a href=\"Holding%20Back%20the%20Flood\"&gt;Holding Back the Flood&lt;/a&gt;\", players had to complete the first two chapters of the &lt;a href=\"Season%20Journey\"&gt;Season Journey&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "49495", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49495", "title": "A Prayer for Salvation", "text": " was the fifth seasonal &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Season%20of%20the%20Malignant\"&gt;Season of the Malignant&lt;/a&gt;\" in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". It activated as soon as \"&lt;a href=\"Answers%20in%20the%20Ashes\"&gt;Answers in the Ashes&lt;/a&gt;\" was completed, and lead directly into \"&lt;a href=\"Hope%27s%20Guardian\"&gt;Hope's Guardian&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
