{"id": "44371", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44371", "title": "Abandoned Prison", "text": "The is the actual prison within &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt; island. The worst prisoners from &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; were condemned here.\nLore.\nStructure.\nThe prison was built into the rocky cliffs of an islet, and connected to the &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint%20Keep\"&gt;keep&lt;/a&gt; on the main island with a &lt;a href=\"Prison%20Lift\"&gt;lift&lt;/a&gt;. A &lt;a href=\"Rotted%20Dock\"&gt;small dock&lt;/a&gt; is located at the entrance of the prison.\nRecent History.\n&lt;a href=\"Timeline%231265\"&gt;Shortly after&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; was destroyed, a shard of it was washed into a &lt;a href=\"Deepstrider%20Lair\"&gt;sea cave&lt;/a&gt; beneath the prison. &lt;a href=\"Woodruh\"&gt;The warden&lt;/a&gt; found it and took it to &lt;a href=\"Warden%27s%20Room\"&gt;his room&lt;/a&gt;. As a result, the shard began to influence the denizens of the prison, and warp them into &lt;a href=\"Transformed%20%28monster%29\"&gt;hideous monsters&lt;/a&gt;. Over time, the whole &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;island&lt;/a&gt; was warped by the power of the corrupted shard.\nTerror's Tide.\nBy &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;1272&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt; attacked Stormpoint, and their legions marched towards the prison; the place they divined to be the location of the shard. The Westmarch soldiers at Stormpoint made a &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint%20Battlement\"&gt;last stand&lt;/a&gt; at the entrance of the prison; both to stop the monstrosities from escaping, and the cultists from reaching their goal.\nIn-game.\nThe is a &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt; zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "21424", "revid": "43594177", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21424", "title": "Abandoned Servant House", "text": "Abandoned Servant House is a small area that can spawn on the north-east side of the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Southern%20Highlands\"&gt;Southern Highlands&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20I%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act I&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\n&lt;a href=\"Arghus%20the%20Collector\"&gt;Arghus the Collector&lt;/a&gt; is located here. Entering this area is required for the achievement &lt;a href=\"No%20Stone%20Unturned\"&gt;No Stone Unturned&lt;/a&gt;. Note that the building can spawn without the Abandoned Servant House being accessible (there is a building, but no entrance). Players should be patient: the building with an open entrance to the Abandoned Servant House is a VERY rare spawn.\u00a0It is believed that it is a 1 in 20 chance to spawn the home, with a 1 in 3 chance to spawn the entrance. In at least 50 attempts, according to one player, the building spawned three times, with one door. It spawned the same time the &lt;a href=\"The%20Scavenged%20Scabbard\"&gt;Scabbard quest&lt;/a&gt; was completed (which is a 1 in 3 for the tower and 1 in 20 for the spawn). In other words, there is a roughly 1.5% chance to spawn both overall."}
