{"id": "44093", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44093", "title": "Aberrant Cinder", "text": "Abherrant Cinders are a form of currency in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\".\nCinders are dropped by &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Helltide\"&gt;Helltide&lt;/a&gt; events, and can be spent to open Helltide Chests scattered through the respective region. These chests boast bountiful boons exclusive to a singular item slot, such as Torso, Legs, or Two-Handed Weapon. If a player is killed, they lose around half of their cinders; they cannot be reclaimed. Furthermore, the cinders expire if the player leaves the Helltide area, or if the timer expires.\nDevelopment.\nOriginally, cinders were dropped on the ground and could be reclaimed."}
