{"id": "42459", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42459", "title": "Aberration", "text": "Aberrations are a &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; class in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nThe Aberrations were created by &lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;. Inside his &lt;a href=\"Library%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;library&lt;/a&gt;. He conjured &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s to use for his experiments in the creation of soulstones. The results of these failed experiments were grotesque aberrations. Demonic &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt; still runs through their veins, and is \"beyond foul\" in its stench.\nHe tried fashioning guardians that would rival &lt;a href=\"Hell\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; for his library out of these remains. The &lt;a href=\"Patchwork%20Maw\"&gt;results&lt;/a&gt; were unpredictable and aggressive, costing Kulle a number of his servants before he locked them in a &lt;a href=\"Writhing%20Ingress\"&gt;section of his library&lt;/a&gt;.\nOver time, some of the demonic remains fused randomly to create &lt;a href=\"Amalgamated%20Dreg\"&gt;amalgamated monsters&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Aberrations are encountered at the Writhing Ingress, within the Library of Zoltun Kulle. The following types exist:\nThey are classified as &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic monsters."}
