{"id": "51989", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51989", "title": "Abyssal Verge", "text": "The is a location in the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Burning Hells&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe Abyssal Verge is located in Hell. A dark shadow referred to as \"Terror Incarnate\" covers the area that is lethal to any &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;mortal&lt;/a&gt; it covers, and many &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s have fallen prey to its encircling grasp. Mortals have seen faces within the watery shadows of the Terror, or perhaps, this is paranoia creeping into their minds.\nC. &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231273\"&gt;1273&lt;/a&gt;, as &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;'s manifestation in &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; drew near, &lt;a href=\"Rayek\"&gt;Rayek&lt;/a&gt; began having nightmares of various locations\u2014twisted and burning red like they were being swallowed by the Hells. On one such dream,he found himself in a warped &lt;a href=\"Wortham\"&gt;Wortham&lt;/a&gt; in front of a portal to the . He sent a letter to summon &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt;, while he went to Wortham to investigate. When the Shard-seeker arrived, they volunteered to enter the portal and purge the evil within. They succeeded and returned with a Terrorwrought Shard. After studying the shard, Rayek (with &lt;a href=\"Charsi\"&gt;Charsi&lt;/a&gt;'s help) built a steady portal to the in the basement of &lt;a href=\"Cain%27s%20Workshop\"&gt;Cain's Workshop&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, fought their way through the Verge to reach the &lt;a href=\"Well%20of%20Hatred\"&gt;Well of Hatred&lt;/a&gt; and defeat the &lt;a href=\"Fell%20Council\"&gt;Fell Council&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nDiablo Immortal.\nThe Abyssal Verge appears as an event in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", as part of the &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20Manifest\"&gt;Nightmare Manifest&lt;/a&gt; update. The event can be entered from Westmarch via a portal next to &lt;a href=\"Rayek\"&gt;Rayek&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"difficulty\"&gt;difficulty&lt;/a&gt; must be Hell II or higher.\nThe portal leads to a map is a variation of one of the overworld maps (such as &lt;a href=\"Ashwold%20Cemetery\"&gt;Ashwold Cemetery&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;. The map chosen remains the same for a certain amount of time, after which it rotates to a different map. After entering the portal, the player appears at a random spawn location along the edge of the map. There is a 30 second countdown for the player to review the map and plan their escape, which can be skipped by clicking on the \"Go\" button. The \"Terror Incarnate\" is a circular field that keeps expanding in diameter, starting near the spawn location and eventually covering the entire map. The player takes damage while inside the circle and gets booted out if staying within it for 15 seconds in a row. After a certain time, the Shade of Destruction appears in the area of the map that is last to be covered by the darkness. Killing this boss results in a victory, awarding an &lt;a href=\"Abyssal%20Essence\"&gt;Abyssal Essence&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhile in the Abyssal Verge, all monsters are marked on the map. A regular monster kill is worth 1 point, an Elite monster is worth 10 points, a Rare Elite is worth 50 points, an Ancient Elite is worth 100 points, and the boss is worth 300 points. The reward increases for every 250 points.\n&lt;a href=\"Normal%20Gems\"&gt;Normal Gems&lt;/a&gt; can be obtained from Abyssal Verge depending on the score. Every 500 points rewards one bound and one unbound normal gem. A player can obtain a maximum of 63 bound and 63 unbound &lt;a href=\"Normal%20Gems\"&gt;Normal Gems&lt;/a&gt; per week from &lt;a href=\"Hidden%20Lair\"&gt;Hidden Lair&lt;/a&gt;s, Abyssal Verge and &lt;a href=\"Erebban\"&gt;Erebban&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nIn the update, the boss spawn was made earlier.\nIn the update, the mob chase distance was increased and their health was decreased.\nThe Normal Gem rewards were added in the update. At the same time, a guaranteed Abyssal Essence drop was added for a score of 1,000 or higher.\nThe update on added a boss location marker to the \"Plan your Escape\" screen, as well as the drops of Normal Gems in a full party.\nDiablo IV.\nThe Abyssal Verge will appear as a zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", as part of the &lt;a href=\"Infernal%20Hordes\"&gt;Infernal Hordes&lt;/a&gt; gameplay mode."}
