{"id": "54636", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54636", "title": "Accursed Tower", "text": ""}
{"id": "45530", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45530", "title": "Accursed Towers", "text": "Accursed Towers is a gameplay mode in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", introduced as part of the &lt;a href=\"Age%20of%20Falling%20Towers\"&gt;Age of Falling Towers&lt;/a&gt; update.\nLore.\n are relics from the time of the ancient &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt; city of &lt;a href=\"Corvus\"&gt;Corvus&lt;/a&gt;. They are mystic seals, placed all over &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, supposedly to protect it from the prying eyes of both &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s. Over time,a curse fell upon most of the towers and they were lost.\nThere are over a hundred scattered all over Sanctuary, with most located in the &lt;a href=\"Dreadlands\"&gt;Dreadlands&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Dry%20Steppes\"&gt;Dry Steppes&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Khanduras\"&gt;Khanduras&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Swamplands\"&gt;Swamplands&lt;/a&gt;.\nRecent History.\nc. &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;1272&lt;/a&gt;, they were unearthed, each exuding an aura of power. The first tower was unearthed on an &lt;a href=\"Bygone%20Islet\"&gt;island&lt;/a&gt; beyond the &lt;a href=\"Gulf%20of%20Westmarch\"&gt;Gulf of Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;. As artifacts were uncovered and returned to &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, whispers of nightmares started to spread, and a request was made for more workers. The dig advanced ahead of schedule, but rumors of nightmares and hallucinations grew among the workers. The dig quickly became a test of wills, one that the workers 'won,' in a sense, as the tower stood revealed. However, claims spread of workers returning with their minds torn.\nThe tower in the Gulf was not the only tower that stood revealed. Sanctuary's denizens desired to claim the powers for themselves, but did not know how to do so. The &lt;a href=\"Immortals\"&gt;Immortals&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shadows\"&gt;Shadows&lt;/a&gt; were among the factions that fought for control of the towers, and &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; also sought to control them.\nGameplay.\nAccursed Towers is features both PvE and PvP gameplay. Clans will compete to claim ownership of towers, thereby providing powerful bonuses to all clan members and the opportunity to acquire new &lt;a href=\"cursed%20item\"&gt;cursed item&lt;/a&gt;s. Players must be in a clan to participate in the mode.\nThe Towers operate under an eight-week &lt;a href=\"season%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;season&lt;/a&gt;. A clan may claim one tower during the first week, and no more than two at any given time. At the end of each season, the ownership of all towers is reset.\nAt the start of a season, players will see many towers on the map to select from, all of which will be Unclaimed Towers. During the first week of a season, from Monday, 3 a.m.\u2013Saturday 7 p.m. server time, the clan's leader and officers can select a tower through the Accursed Towers menu and attempt to claim it for the clan, plunging the Clan into a PvE match against &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt;\u2019s &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;minions&lt;/a&gt; for control of the tower by purifying it.\nPvE.\nWhile fighting demonic hordes for control of the tower, a clan\u2019s objective is to collect Cursed Shards from slain demons. However, players can\u2019t simply attack enemies as they normally would. To deal damage to their foes, players need to locate and activate the tower\u2019s Curse Sources. Doing so will make enemies vulnerable, allowing players to dispatch them and collect their Cursed Shards. Once the timer runs out, the top 10 clan members with the highest Cursed Shard amounts will have them added to their team\u2019s total. A clan can choose to do as many runs to collect Cursed Shards at the same tower as they desire, but only the highest team total will be retained. If a clan has collected the most Cursed Shards among all clans vying for that specific tower by Saturday at 7 p.m. server time, then their clan will claim the tower.\nEven after taking the tower, Hell will attempt to retake it. Once the Corruption meter reaches a certain amount, demonic incursions will follow. Members of the clan must come to defend their tower promptly or else it will be lost and can be reclaimed by another clan.\nThe demons can be warded off by powering up the tower. Within the Accursed Tower's menu, the clan leader and officers can choose to power up their tower. Doing so will not only end the attacks on it from demons but increase the bonuses provided by the tower and periodic rewards provided by the rewards chest inside of it. However, if the tower is powered up, other clans will be able to challenge the owning clan for control of the tower through PvP. Note that Legendary towers (the PvP, Helliquary Reward and Challenge Rift Speed ones) are always open for challenge.\nStarting with the second week of a season, a clan can apply to purify any remaining tower that is not claimed by any clan, including those the owner failed to defend from the curse. Further towers are opened up for purification on weeks 3 and 4 of the season. However each clan can only have two towers under their control. If they wish to challenge another tower, they must choose a tower to relinquish control of should the challenge be successful.\nPvP.\nIn addition to purifying them, clans can gain ownership of towers through challenge. Towers can only be challenged if they are either a Legendary tower or the owning clan has opened them up for challenge. From Saturday, 9 p.m.\u2013Sunday 12 a.m. server time, clans will be able to attempt to challenge for tower ownership from another clan through an all-out PvP match using a 10v10 &lt;a href=\"Conqueror\"&gt;Conqueror&lt;/a&gt; battle format. The clan who wins, in addition to gaining control of the tower, also receives a number of rewards from the match, which can include cursed items. Similarly to claiming a tower by purification, if a clan already has 2 towers under their control, they must choose a tower to replace if they win the match.\nAlliances.\nClans can form tower alliances. This also gives the allied clans access to a \"Tower Alliance\" chat channel.\nTowers are connected with dotted lines on the map. A clan in an alliance can send players to help with defending allied towers connected to the clan's towers.\nThere is no limit on the number of clans in the alliance, however any clans above 3 receive a penalty:\nThe Alliance Leader can transfer towers captured in excess of the limit to other clans.\nList of Towers.\nThere are 9 types of towers.\nNote that Legendary towers (the PvP, Helliquary Reward and Challenge Rift Speed ones) are always open for challenge and therefore don't have \"unboosted\" values of their stats. For the other types of tower, the unboosted stats are included in the table.\nServer Merge.\nDuring a &lt;a href=\"server%20merge\"&gt;server merge&lt;/a&gt;, all Accursed Towers are reset to no owner. The season number is reset to 1. The season start date is updated to the date of the server merge, but the end date is not changed.\nHistory.\nThe alliance feature was added in the update."}
