{"id": "5956", "revid": "26096179", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5956", "title": "Act IV Bestiary", "text": "This is the Act IV Bestiary, the complete list of &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s found in &lt;a href=\"The%20Harrowing\"&gt;Act IV&lt;/a&gt; in the game of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". For complete lists of bestiaries and monsters, see the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II%20Bestiary\"&gt;Diablo II Bestiary&lt;/a&gt;.\nAnalysis.\nThe monsters of Act IV are composed mainly of &lt;a href=\"Demon\"&gt;Demon&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Undead\"&gt;Undead&lt;/a&gt; creatures inhabiting the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;planes of Hell&lt;/a&gt;, while the returning monsters are composed mostly of &lt;a href=\"Animals\"&gt;Animals&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "2513", "revid": "261693", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2513", "title": "Act I (Diablo II)", "text": ""}
{"id": "17682", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17682", "title": "Act I (Diablo III)", "text": "The first &lt;a href=\"Act\"&gt;Act&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" brings players back to &lt;a href=\"Tristram\"&gt;Tristram&lt;/a&gt; and its vicinity, where an &lt;a href=\"Tyreal%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;unknown object&lt;/a&gt; fell from the skies and struck the &lt;a href=\"Tristram%20Cathedral\"&gt;Tristram Cathedral&lt;/a&gt;. After discovering the nature of the \"Fallen Star\" and stopping the threats it caused, attention turns to &lt;a href=\"Coven\"&gt;cultist&lt;/a&gt; activity and the schemes of their leader, &lt;a href=\"Maghda\"&gt;Maghda&lt;/a&gt;. There are numerous references and overlaps with locations and events of previous games, particularly surrounding the fall of King &lt;a href=\"Leoric\"&gt;Leoric&lt;/a&gt;; later, the beginnings of the &lt;a href=\"Nephalem\"&gt;Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; theme are introduced.\nMajor characters include &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Leah\"&gt;Leah&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Tyrael&lt;/a&gt;, and the player's entourage, &lt;a href=\"Kormac\"&gt;Kormac&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lyndon\"&gt;Lyndon&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Haedrig\"&gt;Haedrig&lt;/a&gt;. Act I's &lt;a href=\"bosses\"&gt;bosses&lt;/a&gt; are the &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20King%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Skeleton King&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Queen%20Araneae\"&gt;Queen Araneae&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"The%20Butcher%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;The Butcher&lt;/a&gt;, and its central &lt;a href=\"town\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt; is &lt;a href=\"New%20Tristram\"&gt;New Tristram&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuests.\nThe story begins centered around &lt;a href=\"Leah\"&gt;Leah&lt;/a&gt;, the daughter of &lt;a href=\"Adria\"&gt;Adria&lt;/a&gt; and adopted niece of &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt;, and the defense of the &lt;a href=\"town\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"New%20Tristram\"&gt;New Tristram&lt;/a&gt;. The earliest tasks include putting to rest the undead led by the &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20King%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Skeleton King&lt;/a&gt;, as well as the &lt;a href=\"Khazra\"&gt;Khazra&lt;/a&gt;, and rescuing &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt; and a mysterious man who fell from the sky. The man's sword is broken and scattered; during their retrieval &lt;a href=\"Maghda\"&gt;Maghda&lt;/a&gt; introduces herself along with her &lt;a href=\"Coven\"&gt;Coven&lt;/a&gt;. She eventually kills Cain and kidnaps the fallen stranger, turning the story into a mission of pursuit and revenge. Along the way, hints of &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;'s true power begin to emerge, their first &lt;a href=\"Artisan\"&gt;Artisan&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Followers\"&gt;Followers&lt;/a&gt; are recruited, and the &lt;a href=\"Town%20Portal\"&gt;Town Portal&lt;/a&gt; ability is unlocked. The Act ends with the fallen man revealed to be &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Tyrael&lt;/a&gt;, fallen from &lt;a href=\"heaven\"&gt;heaven&lt;/a&gt;. The heroes vow to pursue Maghda into the east, to avenge Cain's death as well as that of countless townsfolk by stopping her plan to assist the Lesser Evils &lt;a href=\"Belial\"&gt;Belial&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Azmodan\"&gt;Azmodan&lt;/a&gt;.\nIndividual quests, key locations and major events:\nZones and Waypoints.\nAct I takes place in &lt;a href=\"Khanduras\"&gt;Khanduras&lt;/a&gt; in the areas surrounding &lt;a href=\"New%20Tristram\"&gt;New Tristram&lt;/a&gt; (the Act's major &lt;a href=\"town\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt;), the ruins of &lt;a href=\"Old%20Tristram\"&gt;Old Tristram&lt;/a&gt;, and the outlying town of &lt;a href=\"Wortham\"&gt;Wortham&lt;/a&gt;. This includes two major dungeons, those under the &lt;a href=\"Tristram%20Cathedral\"&gt;Tristram Cathedral&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Halls%20of%20Agony\"&gt;Halls of Agony&lt;/a&gt; under &lt;a href=\"Leoric%27s%20Manor\"&gt;Leoric's Manor&lt;/a&gt;.\nNew Tristram.\nThe main quest hub of the zone. The &lt;a href=\"Overlook%20Road\"&gt;Overlook Road&lt;/a&gt; leads to to &lt;a href=\"New%20Tristram\"&gt;New Tristram&lt;/a&gt;, where &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Rumford\"&gt;Captain Rumford&lt;/a&gt; introduces the story.\nOld Tristram.\n&lt;a href=\"Old%20Tristram%20Road\"&gt;Old Tristram Road&lt;/a&gt; leads to &lt;a href=\"Old%20Tristram\"&gt;Old Tristram&lt;/a&gt;, the ruins of Tristram, and eventually to &lt;a href=\"Tristram%20Cathedral\"&gt;Tristram Cathedral&lt;/a&gt;, where &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt; can be recued. Inside the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Cathedral&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Tyrael&lt;/a&gt;'s fall from the &lt;a href=\"High%20Heavens\"&gt;High Heavens&lt;/a&gt; has left a gaping hole through all the levels, shining with an unnatural blue glow. On the last level the &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20King%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Skeleton King (Diablo III)&lt;/a&gt; can be found in his throne room, as well as \"The Stranger\".\nThe Fields of Misery.\nThe second broad area of Act I, north of town, where the player finds the broken crown and two of the three pieces of \"The Stranger's\" sword, as well as &lt;a href=\"Firstborn\"&gt;Ancient Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; ruins.\nThe Highlands.\nA boat can be taken to the small town of &lt;a href=\"Wortham\"&gt;Wortham&lt;/a&gt;, north of which the Highlands lead to the area around &lt;a href=\"Leoric%27s%20Manor\"&gt;Leoric's Manor&lt;/a&gt;. The area is dominated by &lt;a href=\"Khazra\"&gt;Khazra&lt;/a&gt; as well as other wild monsters. The zones in order are:\nThe Halls of Agony.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Halls%20of%20Agony\"&gt;Halls of Agony&lt;/a&gt; can be found under &lt;a href=\"Leoric%27s%20Manor\"&gt;Leoric's Manor&lt;/a&gt;. This is where the &lt;a href=\"Coven\"&gt;Coven&lt;/a&gt; has imprisoned &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Tyrael&lt;/a&gt;. The final boss of Act I is the horrific, murdering demon &lt;a href=\"The%20Butcher%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;The Butcher&lt;/a&gt; which must be defeated to free him.\nPre-release.\nDuring promotion before the release of \"Diablo III\", the official website stated that the \"Fallen Star\" was a 'harbinger of doom' that would awaken ancient evils, calling for heroes of &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; to defend their world. Only some parts of Act I were revealed. The demo allowed play of the quests up to the first &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20King%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Skeleton King&lt;/a&gt;."}
