{"id": "53348", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53348", "title": "Ah Bulan", "text": "Ah Bulan is a &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Guardian\"&gt;Spirit Guardian&lt;/a&gt; known as the Mender of Veils. He wanders throughout &lt;a href=\"Nahantu\"&gt;Nahantu&lt;/a&gt;\u2014and at times beyond, and is a very hard spirit to find. In the latter part of the year, it goes on a fallow walk through the &lt;a href=\"Field%20of%20Giants\"&gt;Field of Giants&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nDuring a &lt;a href=\"Trial%20of%20Mists\"&gt;Trial of Mists&lt;/a&gt;, one of Ah Bulan's spirits spared an unclaimed boy. The boy told the spirit he would follow him always. This remained true even after Ah Bulan called the spirit home. At a point in the past, Ah Bulan protected the people of Nahantu from otherworldly entities, and gifted the survivors with a silver of his power. As a result, some began to worship him.\nVessel of Hatred.\nBy &lt;a href=\"timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Eru\"&gt;Eru&lt;/a&gt;\u2014following the advice of &lt;a href=\"Akarat\"&gt;Akarat&lt;/a&gt;'s spirit, led to seek Ah Bulan. After getting permission from the council, they opened a tear at his shrine in &lt;a href=\"Wekenga\"&gt;Wekenga&lt;/a&gt; to Ah Bulan's domain in the Spirit Realm. Meanwhile, Ah Bulan was being attacked by &lt;a href=\"the%20Hollows\"&gt;the Hollows&lt;/a&gt; created by &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;'s taint.\nBy the time they reached Ah Bulan's domain within the Spirit Realm, he had already be driven mad by the corruption, and had to be killed.\nLegacy.\nAfter his death, Eru\u2014with grief, carved Ah Bulan's heart to give to &lt;a href=\"Neyrelle\"&gt;Neyrelle&lt;/a&gt;. Consuming it gave her the strength to keep on resisting Mephisto's influence. This\u2014along with Neyrelle accidentally killing &lt;a href=\"Maka\"&gt;Maka&lt;/a&gt; later on, were the seeds of hatred Mephisto would eventually use to turn Eru.\nAppearance.\nAh Bulan takes the form of a leonid centaur. He has long hair in thick dreadlocks, and covers his face with an avian mask. Ah Bulan wields a spear and shield to battle. When tainted by &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;'s corruption, his lion half is coated with tar."}
{"id": "47542", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47542", "title": "Ahavarion", "text": "Ahavarion is a &lt;a href=\"spears\"&gt;spear&lt;/a&gt; once wielded by the &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Lycander\"&gt;Lycander&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nLycander was among the &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;s who followed &lt;a href=\"Inarius\"&gt;Inarius&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. There, she fell in love with the &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Philios%20%28Nephalem%29\"&gt;Philios&lt;/a&gt;. After &lt;a href=\"the%20Purge\"&gt;the Purge&lt;/a&gt;, she fled to &lt;a href=\"Heaven\"&gt;Heaven&lt;/a&gt;, but left Ahavarion behind, such was her love for Philios, and her hope that the spear would help bring peace to Sanctuary. She imbued some of her power within the spear.\nMillennia later, Ahavarion remained in the care of the &lt;a href=\"Oracle%20Caste\"&gt;Oracle Caste&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nAhavarion has appeared as an in-game item in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;IV&lt;/a&gt;\":"}
