{"id": "49518", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49518", "title": "Aisah", "text": "Aisah was a member of the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Cult of Damnation&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nAisah played a pocket lyre.\nIn/around &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, Aisah and her daughter, &lt;a href=\"Luzja\"&gt;Luzja&lt;/a&gt;, were on &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;, along with &lt;a href=\"Razmus\"&gt;Razmus&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Omer\"&gt;Omer&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Laksmi\"&gt;Laksmi&lt;/a&gt;. Laksmi noted that Aisah seemed off, and her suspicions were well-founded as Aisah handed over her fellow travellers to the cult (she also apparently intended on handing over Luzjah as well). Aisah left with &lt;a href=\"Vizibor\"&gt;Vizibor&lt;/a&gt;, who empowered her in a ritual, as Aisah had proven her dedication to the cult. However, she was slain almost immediately afterwards by an &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;. Her pocket lyre was returned to Luzja, who was kept ignorant as to how far into darkness Aisah had fallen.\nIn-game.\nAisah appears as a &lt;a href=\"Super%20Unique%20Monster\"&gt;Super Unique Monster&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" in the &lt;a href=\"side%20quest\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Bond\"&gt;The Bond&lt;/a&gt;.\" She is a &lt;a href=\"Damned%20Cultist\"&gt;Damned Cultist&lt;/a&gt;, but bereft of any special properties."}
