{"id": "47519", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47519", "title": "Akarat (Paladin)", "text": "Akarat was a proud &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; and member of the &lt;a href=\"Knights%20of%20Westmarch\"&gt;Knights of Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;. He was young, headstrong, and eager to prove his worth.\nBiography.\nAkarat was born in &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231255\"&gt;1255&lt;/a&gt; and was named after the &lt;a href=\"Akarat\"&gt;founder of Zakarum&lt;/a&gt;. He patrolled &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; and engaged in ring bouts, but due to the timing of his birth, never saw actual battle. In &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231265\"&gt;1265&lt;/a&gt;, after the destruction of &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Arreat\"&gt;Mount Arreat&lt;/a&gt;, he heard stories from men who had returned from the &lt;a href=\"Dreadlands\"&gt;Dreadlands&lt;/a&gt;. He wanted to be just like them. \nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;1272&lt;/a&gt;, Akarat left &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt; to follow rumors about the &lt;a href=\"End%20of%20Days\"&gt;End of Days&lt;/a&gt;. Cain told Akarat of the &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic invasion he feared was coming, and unlike so many others, Akarat believed him. As they travelled across &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, he was eager to hear Cain's stories, and the two stayed up long after they should have entered slumber.\nThe two entered the &lt;a href=\"Borderlands\"&gt;Borderlands&lt;/a&gt;, where they came across a &lt;a href=\"Vizjerei\"&gt;Vizjerei&lt;/a&gt; repository. They entered it, and sensed they were not alone. Cain warned Akarat to ignore whatever voice he might hear, and asked him to guard the entrance. Despite Akarat's unease due to Cain's age, Cain assured him he would be alright. He would deal with whatever was in the repository, Akarat would guard against anything coming at them from outside.\nDespite this, the true threat was a &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; who lurked inside the repository. Akarat drew his &lt;a href=\"swords\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt; against the creature, but it simply passed through its smoke-like body. The demon swirled around Akarat, showing him terrible visions, and whispered terrible things about Cain and Akarat himself. Cain used an &lt;a href=\"Ammuit\"&gt;Ammuit&lt;/a&gt; spell to buy them some time, but despite Cain's urgings, Akarat swore to kill the demon. To avenge &lt;a href=\"Khalim\"&gt;Khalim&lt;/a&gt; and the corruption of Zakarum. \nThe demon took Akarat's own form, and the Paladin again drew his sword, and again, to no avail. The demon possessed him, and while Akarat was able to regain some control with Cain's urging, it was not enough. Cain was able to banish the demon to Hell, albeit while still possessing Akarat's body.\nIn-game.\nAkarat is seen as an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". He is briefly featured in the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;, \"&lt;a href=\"Fare%20You%20Well\"&gt;Fare You Well&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
