{"id": "52827", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52827", "title": "Aldkin", "text": "Aldkin is a &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; child, and member of the &lt;a href=\"Pale%20Hand\"&gt;Pale Hand&lt;/a&gt;. He has the ability to metamorphize between his human and demon forms. \nBiography.\nA half-child, half-demon creature, Aldkin was born part-demonic as a result of the &lt;a href=\"First%20Khazra\"&gt;First Khazra&lt;/a&gt; within the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Citadel\"&gt;Dark Citadel&lt;/a&gt; performing dark rituals on his mother. \nIn-game.\nAldkin is a hirable mercenary in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", introduced in the \"&lt;a href=\"Vessel%20of%20Hatred\"&gt;Vessel of Hatred&lt;/a&gt;\" expansion. He is a human child with the ability to turn into a demon. His basic attack is hurling fireballs at a target.\nPer the Pale Hand's bartering system, levelling up Aldkin's rapport will grant players access to resource-based &lt;a href=\"items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt;\nAbilities.\nAldkin's skill tree is divided between fire and shadow magic. His fire attacks are based on dealing direct damage, while his shadow abilities are themed around curses, causing enemies to scatter."}
