{"id": "31928", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31928", "title": "Aletur", "text": "Aletur, The Howling Storm, is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"The%20Unclean\"&gt;Unclean One&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"Ruins%20of%20Sescheron\"&gt;Ruins of Sescheron&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiography.\nAletur was a denizen of &lt;a href=\"Sescheron\"&gt;Sescheron&lt;/a&gt;. In regards to a &lt;a href=\"Bracers%20of%20the%20First%20Men\"&gt;set of bracers&lt;/a&gt; in his possession, he declared that he did not care about their origins, only that they helped him defeat his enemies.\nAfter the &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20Sescheron\"&gt;Siege of Sescheron&lt;/a&gt;, he survived as a flesh-eater, driven mad in the years to come.\nIn-game.\nAletur can randomly spawn in the Ruins of Sescheron. It appears that he &lt;a href=\"dual-wield\"&gt;dual-wield&lt;/a&gt;s two huge blades that do not visually match any in-game weapons.\nLike other Barbarian cannibals, Aletur has very high melee damage, huge &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt; pool and moves very quickly. In addition, he has skill that deals damage upon landing, and summons multiple &lt;a href=\"Primeval%20Hunter\"&gt;Pack Hunter&lt;/a&gt; wolves at his side in the beginning of combat. He has no monster affixes, though.\nThe flavor text of the &lt;a href=\"Bracers%20of%20the%20First%20Men\"&gt;Bracers of the First Men&lt;/a&gt; is narrated by him."}
