{"id": "37602", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37602", "title": "Allen Adham", "text": "Allen Adham is the head of &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20Entertainment\"&gt;Blizzard Entertainment&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Incubation\"&gt;Incubation&lt;/a&gt; team.\nBiography.\nAdham is one of the three original founders of Blizzard, alongside Frank Pearce and Mike Morhaime. He ran the company for thirteen years. In the last few years of his time at Blizzard, he was both running the company and overseeing development of \"&lt;a href=\"World%20of%20Warcraft\"&gt;World of Warcraft&lt;/a&gt;\" as lead game designer. Exhausted by 6-7 day weeks, Adham left Blizzard just after WOW was released to start a hedge fund, using artificial intelligence to trade the stock market (Adham has commented that this was another \"video game\" for him). About one to two years into the job, Adham came to regret his decision, missing work on working on videogame work. However, it gave him a good work-life balance. He returned to Blizzard in 2016."}
{"id": "48316", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48316", "title": "Alley of Blood", "text": "Alley of Blood is a recurring PvP event in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is the battle format for &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20War\"&gt;Shadow War&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Vigil%20of%20Blades\"&gt;Vigil of Blades&lt;/a&gt; component of &lt;a href=\"Cycle%20of%20Strife\"&gt;Cycle of Strife&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is currently running from July 12, 3 a.m.\u2013July 19, 3 a.m. server time, 2024.\nGameplay.\nAlley of Blood is a MOBA-style battle a single lane and turrets on both sides. The goal of each team is to destroy the other team's turrets and Crystal Heart. Sacred Guardians spawn as NPCs that fight on the side of their respective team.\nDefeated players drop Champion's Marks that increase character power. A player also drops a portion of their current Champion's Marks upon being killed.\nSpecialist Skills.\nThese skills are available only during the Alley of Blood event. Each player can only use one, and each team can only have skills from the same category selected by two players, but those two players may select the same skill from that category.\nThe skills have a cooldown of 60 or 90 seconds.\nLimited time event.\nThe limited time event of Alley of Blood was a 4v4 version. Players could earn rewards for the following tasks:\nDevelopment.\nAlley of Blood was introduced in the September 21 2023 update, replacing the battle format for Shadow War. The standalone, 4v4 version was available during the last week of &lt;a href=\"Season%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29%23Season%2017\"&gt;Season 17&lt;/a&gt; and the first week of &lt;a href=\"Season%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29%23Season%2018\"&gt;Season 18&lt;/a&gt;."}
