{"id": "47105", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47105", "title": "Alma", "text": "Alma is a refugee from &lt;a href=\"Caldeum\"&gt;Caldeum&lt;/a&gt;.\nCharacter.\nAlma is a loving mother, who cares a lot for her children. She broke down into tears when she was separated from them in a sandstorm. She is also very affectionate, and hugged her children on different occasions in order to comfort them.\nBiography.\nAlma lived with her husband &lt;a href=\"Kaapo\"&gt;Kaapo&lt;/a&gt;, and children &lt;a href=\"Bahar\"&gt;Bahar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ram\"&gt;Ram&lt;/a&gt;, in Caldeum. For reasons not mentioned, her whole family had to leave in a hurry. They migrated to &lt;a href=\"Shassar%20Sea\"&gt;Shassar Sea&lt;/a&gt;.\nShortly after they arrived Kaapo ran afoul with the local gang; the &lt;a href=\"Sand%20Scorpions\"&gt;Sand Scorpions&lt;/a&gt;, and she had to take the children and escape to safety. They were then caught in a sandstorm, where she was separated from her children.\nAfter finding out that her children were missing she wept in grief. Shortly after, an adventurer passed by. She pleaded with them to help her search for her children. As they retraced her steps they found the children's toys in the sand. Fortunately, Bahar and Ram were hiding beneath the skeletal remains of a large beast, where they took shelter from the storm.\nThe children were then attacked by &lt;a href=\"Desert%20Crawler\"&gt;Desert Crawler&lt;/a&gt;s, but were protected by the adventurer. After showing their gratitude, the children expressed concern for their fathers whereabouts. As Alma comforted them, the adventurer volunteered to look for Kaapo. They returned with news that Kaapo was killed, but the Sand Scorpion camp had been decimated.\nIn-game.\nAlma is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;. She can occasionally be seen weeping in the &lt;a href=\"Windswept%20Sands\"&gt;Windswept Sands&lt;/a&gt;. Talking to her initiates the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20Side%20Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt;, \"&lt;a href=\"No%20Place%20for%20Children\"&gt;No Place for Children&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "6473", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6473", "title": "Alma Negra", "text": "Alma Negra is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Sacred%20Rondache\"&gt;Sacred Rondache&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Paladin%20Shields\"&gt;shield&lt;/a&gt; from \"\", exclusive only to the &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe shield was historically presented to &lt;a href=\"Akkhan\"&gt;Akkhan&lt;/a&gt; alongside the &lt;a href=\"Piro%20Marella\"&gt;Piro Marella&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlthough Alma Negra does not bestow as much skill bonus as the &lt;a href=\"Herald%20of%20Zakarum\"&gt;Herald of Zakarum&lt;/a&gt;, it does have other bonuses that make up for it.\nAlma Negra tends to be more of an offensive-heavy than defensive-heavy shield. Particularly notable is its bonuses to &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Rating\"&gt;Attack Rating&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Damage\"&gt;Damage&lt;/a&gt;, both of which can be very high for a shield. When combined with &lt;a href=\"Offensive%20Auras\"&gt;Offensive Auras&lt;/a&gt; such as &lt;a href=\"Conviction\"&gt;Conviction&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Fanaticism\"&gt;Fanaticism&lt;/a&gt;, the Alma Negra can be a big help for Paladins inclined to be more physical fighters.\nDefensively, however, Alma Negra is just a bit lacking. It does not give any bonuses to &lt;a href=\"resistances\"&gt;resistances&lt;/a&gt;, which could be harmful in or &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;difficulties&lt;/a&gt;. Similarly, its &lt;a href=\"Block\"&gt;Chance to Block&lt;/a&gt; is lower than other &lt;a href=\"shields\"&gt;shields&lt;/a&gt;.\nAlma Negra is still a useful shield, especially for Paladins such as &lt;a href=\"Zealot%20%28build%29\"&gt;Zealots&lt;/a&gt;. Some may choose to help remedy the resistance problem by &lt;a href=\"socket\"&gt;socket&lt;/a&gt;ing it and then inserting a Perfect &lt;a href=\"Diamond\"&gt;Diamond&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Um%20Rune\"&gt;Um Rune&lt;/a&gt;.\nStats.\nDefense: 461-511\nRequired Level: 77\nRequired Strength: 109\nChance To Block: 78%\n&lt;a href=\"Smite\"&gt;Smite&lt;/a&gt; Damage: 35 To 58\nDurability: 68"}
