{"id": "44267", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44267", "title": "Altar of Lilith", "text": "Altars of Lilith are shrines dedicated to &lt;a href=\"Lilith\"&gt;Lilith&lt;/a&gt;. Created by &lt;a href=\"the%20Ancients\"&gt;the Ancients&lt;/a&gt;, they could still be found in &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Enmity\"&gt;Great Enmity&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nAltars of Lilith are found in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\" in open-world areas. Finding a shrine gives a permanent buff to all of the player's characters on a realm server that correspond to the same gameplay type. For instance, unlocking an altar in &lt;a href=\"Hardcore\"&gt;Hardcore&lt;/a&gt; applies the buff to all Hardcore characters, but not regular ones, and vice versa. To gain the buff, players must complete a challenge. Each challenge completed also grants the player &lt;a href=\"renown\"&gt;renown&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe altars are not found in &lt;a href=\"Nahantu\"&gt;Nahantu&lt;/a&gt;, and their role is taken by &lt;a href=\"Tenets%20of%20Akarat\"&gt;Tenets of Akarat&lt;/a&gt;.\nDevelopment.\nThe altars were not present in \"\" as players were frustrated with the original altars giving stat bonuses."}
{"id": "48332", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48332", "title": "Altar of Martyrdom", "text": "The Altar of Martyrdom is a shrine located on the &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Judgment\"&gt;Fields of Judgment&lt;/a&gt;. It is among the shrines visited by &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Light\"&gt;Cathedral of Light&lt;/a&gt; penitents when undertaking a pilgrimage.\nIn-game.\nThe Altar of Martyrdom is a sub-zone of the Fields of Judgment in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". It plays a role in the \"&lt;a href=\"Pilgrimage\"&gt;Pilgrimage&lt;/a&gt;\" . The &lt;a href=\"tome\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"To%20the%20Sufferer\"&gt;To the Sufferer&lt;/a&gt;\" is found here."}
{"id": "48327", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48327", "title": "Altar of Purity", "text": "The Altar of Purity is a &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Light\"&gt;Cathedral of Light&lt;/a&gt; altar located in the &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Judgment\"&gt;Fields of Judgment&lt;/a&gt;. It is the first altar that Cathedral penitents will visit when undertaking a redemptive pilgrimage. Here, they will pick up the Idol of the Faithful.\nIn-game.\nThe Altar of Purity is a sub-zone of the Fields of Judgment in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". Players must visit it during the \"&lt;a href=\"Pilgrimage\"&gt;Pilgrimage&lt;/a&gt;,\" where they obtain the &lt;a href=\"Idol%20of%20the%20Faithful\"&gt;Idol of the Faithful&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"tome\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"To%20the%20Sinner\"&gt;To the Sinner&lt;/a&gt;\" is also found here."}
