{"id": "46680", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46680", "title": "Amalgam of Rage", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"%20demon\"&gt; demon&lt;/a&gt;ic fiend created by &lt;a href=\"Lilith\"&gt;Lilith&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Nafain\"&gt;Nafain&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt;. It represents Nafain's hatred of the &lt;a href=\"Pale%20Knight\"&gt;Pale Knight&lt;/a&gt;s, and the &lt;a href=\"Cathedral%20of%20Light\"&gt;Cathedral of Light&lt;/a&gt; for their part in making the culture of &lt;a href=\"druid\"&gt;druid&lt;/a&gt;ism to be forgotten in &lt;a href=\"Scosglen\"&gt;Scosglen&lt;/a&gt;. It was gifted to &lt;a href=\"Astaroth\"&gt;Astaroth&lt;/a&gt; to use as a mount.\nBiography.\nIn order to find the burial site of Astaroth's &lt;a href=\"soulstone\"&gt;soulstone&lt;/a&gt;, Lilith payed the druid Nafain a visit. Playing on his hatred of the Pale Knights, she made a pact with him, and agreed to wipe out the Knight Penitent at &lt;a href=\"Cerrigar\"&gt;Cerrigar&lt;/a&gt;; Nafain's hometown. In a means to kill two birds with one stone she cut the druid in two, and bound his torso to a tree in the moors at &lt;a href=\"Daudur%20Peats\"&gt;Daudur Peats&lt;/a&gt;. The tree corrupted his body and prevented him from dying from blood loss. His &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt; flowed through area, corrupting and/or killing the flora and &lt;a href=\"animal\"&gt;fauna&lt;/a&gt; within its reach. Lilith channeled the blood and corruption to a nearby cave, where they began to gestate into the amalgam.\n disrupted the gestation before it was completed. Fortunately, it was almost completed and the emerged, with bone and sinew partly exposed. After it was injured by the Wanderer in a short battle, Lilith recalled it.\nLilith led the beast to attack &lt;a href=\"Eldhaime%20Keep\"&gt;Eldhaime Keep&lt;/a&gt;. After tearing right through its defenders, Lilith led it to Astaroth's soulstone beneath the keep. When Astaroth was freed, the Amalgam was gifted to him as a mount. She then took them to Cerrigar. This was to make Astaroth fight harder to consume his &lt;a href=\"Yorin\"&gt;host&lt;/a&gt;, and to complete her pact with Nafain. The amalgam, with Astaroth as its rider, decimated most of the knights at Cerrigar (and the rest of the town). It was later killed along with its rider by the Wanderer.\nIn-game.\nThe is a boss &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". It mainly attacks with bites, claw swipes and pounces. It also has a &lt;a href=\"fear\"&gt;terrifying&lt;/a&gt; howl that summons nearby canines to fight for it. When being ridden by Astaroth, the demon can make his mount breath &lt;a href=\"fire\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; from the mouths of its three most prominent heads by channeling his flames through it."}
{"id": "45338", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45338", "title": "Amalgamated Dreg", "text": "s are a type of &lt;a href=\"aberration\"&gt;aberration&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nDemonic remains unsuited to &lt;a href=\"Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;'s experiments filled waste piles before their natural value became clear to the mad mage. The diversity of dregs' component parts has increased over the centuries, and brutal pincers used to cripple intruders are their only mainstay.\nIn-game.\ns can be found at the &lt;a href=\"Writhing%20Ingress\"&gt;Writhing Ingress&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Library%20of%20Zoltun%20Kulle\"&gt;Library of Zoltun Kulle&lt;/a&gt;. They attack at range by spitting a barrage of &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; from their pincers, or with claws at melee."}
