{"id": "3612", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3612", "title": "Amn Rune", "text": "An Amn rune is a low &lt;a href=\"Runes\"&gt;rune&lt;/a&gt; which can be &lt;a href=\"socket\"&gt;socket&lt;/a&gt;ed into equipment in \"\". Amn runes are common, but useful for the &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Spirit rune word&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt; recipes such as &lt;a href=\"Crafted%20Items\"&gt;crafting&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"List%20of%20Blood%20Items\"&gt;Blood&lt;/a&gt; amulets.\nEffects.\nSocketing an item with an Amn rune increases the item's level requirement to 25, unless it was already higher.\nSources.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Countess\"&gt;The Countess&lt;/a&gt;'s extra rune drops on nightmare or hell difficulty can include Amn runes.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Hellforge\"&gt;Hellforge&lt;/a&gt; on normal difficulty has a 1 in 11 chance to drop an Amn rune as part of its quest reward. Amn is the highest rune that normal Hellforge can drop.\nThe Act 4 Good treasure class has a chance to drop an Amn rune, as do higher Good treasure classes.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt; can transmute three &lt;a href=\"Thul%20Rune\"&gt;Thul runes&lt;/a&gt; and one chipped topaz into one Amn rune.\nRune Words.\nAmn runes are used in these &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Words\"&gt;rune words&lt;/a&gt;:\nRecipes.\nAmn runes are used in eight &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt; recipes."}
