{"id": "51970", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=51970", "title": "Ancestral Properties", "text": ""}
{"id": "47958", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47958", "title": "Ancestral Tableau", "text": " is a gameplay feature in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is part of the &lt;a href=\"Seeker%27s%20Path\"&gt;Seeker's Path&lt;/a&gt; interface.\nThe Tableau provides bonuses to Strength, Intelligence, Willpower, Vitality, Fortitude and &lt;a href=\"Combat%20Rating\"&gt;Combat Rating&lt;/a&gt;. The attributes are increased by earning Activity Points from &lt;a href=\"Defense%20of%20Cyrangar\"&gt;Defense of Cyrangar&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Purge%20the%20Depths\"&gt;Purge the Depths&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt; raids, &lt;a href=\"Bounties\"&gt;Bounties&lt;/a&gt;, s and &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Rift\"&gt;Elder Rift&lt;/a&gt;s. The points earned are increased when doing these with Warbands, Friends or Clans. The amount of points gained depends on the difference between the current Seeker Rating and the Server Seeker Rating, which increases by 10 per week. Players below the server rating get a boosted increase, while players above it are penalized.\nEvery 300 activity points are automatically converted into 5 Seeker Rating and 1 in each of the 5 stats.\nHistory.\nOriginally, the Tableau was part of the &lt;a href=\"Warband\"&gt;Warband&lt;/a&gt; interface, and provided a direct &lt;a href=\"Combat%20Rating\"&gt;Combat Rating&lt;/a&gt; bonus plus the stat bonuses when upgraded.\n&lt;a href=\"Ancestral%20Weapons\"&gt;Ancestral Weapons&lt;/a&gt; needed to be placed in the Tableau, and their attributes served as a cap for the bonuses from the Tableau. This was removed in the &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20Manifest\"&gt;Nightmare Manifest&lt;/a&gt; update, after which the Tableau simply provided bonuses based on its upgrade level.\nGetting the bonuses required joining a warband, and even though the upgrades stayed when changing warbands, a player who quit their warband would temporarily lose the bonus, and had to join a new warband and earn 400 warband activity points to reactivate the bonus. In the update, it was moved to the newly introduced &lt;a href=\"Seeker%27s%20Path\"&gt;Seeker's Path&lt;/a&gt;, and the warband-related aspects were dropped. \"Warband Activity Points\" were renamed to \"Activity Points\".\nOriginally, Activity Points had a weekly cap of 1500, with the first 1000 points obtained at a 4x rate. Each upgrade of the Tableau cost 300 points (with the first few upgrades costing less), but the stats and Combat Rating gained was decreased depending on the player's tableau level compared to the server's level. In the update, the weekly cap was removed, each upgrade was fixed to provide 1 point in the five stats and 5 Seeker Rating, and instead the reduction was applied to the activity points themselves."}
{"id": "48384", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48384", "title": "Ancestral Tableu", "text": ""}
{"id": "43827", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43827", "title": "Ancestral Weapons", "text": "Ancestral Weapons were a gameplay feature of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", introduced in the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Nightmares\"&gt;Forgotten Nightmares&lt;/a&gt; update.\nLore.\nAncestral weapons were recovered with the claiming of &lt;a href=\"Castle%20Cyrangar\"&gt;Castle Cyrangar&lt;/a&gt; by a &lt;a href=\"warband\"&gt;warband&lt;/a&gt;. Unfortunately, some of the weapons had fallen into &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic hands.\nGameplay.\nAncestral Weapons had a chance to drop in any zone in the game, but the highest drop rates were in the &lt;a href=\"Purge%20the%20Depths\"&gt;Purge the Depths&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Defense%20of%20Cyrangar\"&gt;Defense of Cyrangar&lt;/a&gt; game modes.\nTo harness the power of these weapons, you had to place them into the Ancestral Tableau, located in the heart of Castle Cyrangar. Once placed, Ancestral Weapons conferred a portion of their attributes, such as &lt;a href=\"Combat%20Rating\"&gt;Combat Rating&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"strength\"&gt;strength&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"intelligence\"&gt;intelligence&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"vitality\"&gt;vitality&lt;/a&gt; onto all members of the &lt;a href=\"warband\"&gt;warband&lt;/a&gt;. Every warband member could contribute any number of items and use those in the Warband Stash. The stats only served as a cap, and the actual stats needed to be upgraded by spending Warband Activity points.\nIn addition to the bonus attributes, players could also call upon special powers from the warband's Ancestral Weapons while donning &lt;a href=\"Invocation%20Gear\"&gt;Invocation Gear&lt;/a&gt;. All gear that drops had a chance to possess an additional Invocation property. Invocation Gear could be equipped to the player's character in its respective item slot to receive the benefit and trigger the ability of your Ancestral Weapon. \nFor example, an Ancestral Weapon might provide the property:\n\"Deal Lightning damage to surrounding enemies.\"\nWhen combined with an Invocation such as:\n\"Chance to trigger your Ancestral Property when you deal damage.\"\nIt results in the combined ability:\n\"Chance to deal lightning damage to surrounding enemies when you deal damage.\"\nAncestral Properties.\nAncestral Weapons must be enshrined at the Tableau for their ability to be activated by an Invocation.\nHistory.\nOriginally each warband member could only place one Ancestral Weapon in the tableau. This was changed such that every player can contribute any number of items and use those in the Warband Stash.\nAncestral Weapons were removed in the &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20Manifest\"&gt;Nightmare Manifest&lt;/a&gt; update. Existing weapons from the Tableau were returned to their owners, and the Tableau now only provides a bonus based on the upgrade with Warband Activity points."}
