{"id": "49928", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49928", "title": "Ancient Skull", "text": "The Ancient Skull is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Season%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Season of Blood&lt;/a&gt;\" in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\".\nBiography.\nOrigins.\nIn life, the skull was a &lt;a href=\"Firstborn\"&gt;Firstborn&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt;. It pledged itself to Lord &lt;a href=\"Zir\"&gt;Zir&lt;/a&gt;, who promised his followers immortality. The nephalem, now a &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; (and a powerful one at that) apparently descended into the &lt;a href=\"City%20of%20the%20Ancients\"&gt;City of the Ancients&lt;/a&gt; to follow Zir into slumber. However, something apparently went wrong, as the vampire's skull was separated from its body, and the skull itself placed in the &lt;a href=\"Fetid%20Mausoleum\"&gt;Fetid Mausoleum&lt;/a&gt;.\nSeason of Blood.\n&lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;Eons later&lt;/a&gt;, the skull was retrieved from the mausoleum and drenched in &lt;a href=\"potent%20blood\"&gt;potent blood&lt;/a&gt;, reviving it. The skull was aghast, in that not only was its body missing, but that Zir's promises of immortality had turned out to be bunk. It beheld the &lt;a href=\"Erys\"&gt;two&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"The%20Wanderer%20%28Diablo%20IV%29\"&gt;humans&lt;/a&gt; before it, and could tell that Zir had tried to turn the latter into a vampire. The skull agreed to help the pair kill Zir, after which, it would sleep. To this end, it opened a portal to the City of the Ancients. The pair passed through, but quickly returned, as they were unable to progress through the city.\nThe skull advised the Wanderer that if they wished to defeat the undying, they too would have to become undying themselves. More specifically, it advised them to slay Zir's &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Seekers\"&gt;Blood Seekers&lt;/a&gt; and cripple his forces. The Wanderer departed, and while they were gone, the skull noticed that Erys \"learnt something,\" apparently by going over various texts. Whatever the case, Erys departed, leaving the skull alone.\nAt some point after Erys left, the office was ransacked by Zir's Bloodseekers, and the skull was knocked out of its basin, and the blood keeping it 'alive.' The Wanderer returned, slew the Bloodseekers, placed the skull back in the basin, and used their own blood to revive it. The skull told them that Erys had departed, and told them that they reeked of vampirism. That they were becoming more and more like Zir, and Erys didn't like it.\nAfter the Wanderer left, Erys left as well to pursue her own agenda. When she returned to the office, she found that the skull was missing.\nIn-game.\nThe Ancient Skull technically first appears as an item in the form of the &lt;a href=\"Profane%20Vampire%20Skull\"&gt;Profane Vampire Skull&lt;/a&gt;. Curiously enough, the item's image depicts what appears to be a standard human skull, bereft of a vampire's telltale fangs.\nThe Ancient Skull, once revived, serves as an NPC in the &lt;a href=\"Magistrate%27s%20Office\"&gt;Magistrate's Office&lt;/a&gt; sub-zone in &lt;a href=\"Ked%20Bardu\"&gt;Ked Bardu&lt;/a&gt;."}
