{"id": "31200", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31200", "title": "Andariel, the Maiden of Anguish", "text": "Andariel, the Maiden of Anguish is a &lt;a href=\"Tomes\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt; found in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIt is found in one of &lt;a href=\"Cain%27s%20Lost%20Satchel\"&gt;Cain's Lost Satchel&lt;/a&gt;s. Reading it adds to the &lt;a href=\"Judge%20of%20Character\"&gt;Judge of Character&lt;/a&gt; achievement.\nIt reads as follows:\n\"&lt;a href=\"Andariel\"&gt;Andariel&lt;/a&gt; was the only female &lt;a href=\"Great%20Evils\"&gt;Evil&lt;/a&gt;. She aided the &lt;a href=\"Lesser%20Evils\"&gt;Lesser Evils&lt;/a&gt; for many years, but eventually she lost faith in their plots. &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231264\"&gt;Two decades ago&lt;/a&gt;, she chose to help &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt; during his resurgence and seized the &lt;a href=\"Citadel%20of%20the%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Citadel of the Sightless Eye&lt;/a&gt;. Ultimately, she perished at the hands of &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;brave heroes&lt;/a&gt;. - &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt;\""}
