{"id": "7157", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7157", "title": "Annihilus", "text": "The Annihilus is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Charm\"&gt;Charm&lt;/a&gt; dropped by &lt;a href=\"Uber%20Diablo\"&gt;Uber Diablo&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Battle.net\"&gt;Battle.net&lt;/a&gt; realms. Characters may possess only one such charm in their inventory space.\nThe Annihilus is the only small charm to offer +skills and +all stats, as well as a significant chunk of +all resistances. Even if it rolls its worst possible stats, it still grants far more to players than any magical charm in terms of power and survivability. In addition, this item holds the honor of being one of only two items to grant a bonus to earned &lt;a href=\"Experience\"&gt;Experience&lt;/a&gt;, the other being &lt;a href=\"Ondal%27s%20Wisdom\"&gt;Ondal's Wisdom&lt;/a&gt;. \nThis item uses the sprite for &lt;a href=\"Mephisto%27s%20Soulstone\"&gt;Mephisto's Soulstone&lt;/a&gt;, despite a sprite for a red-colored \"Diablo's &lt;a href=\"Soulstone\"&gt;Soulstone&lt;/a&gt;\" having existed in the game at the time of creation which could have given it a more unique appearance.\nStats.\nRequired Level: 70"}
